title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine meat, celery, bread crumbs, garlic, egg, salt and water. Shape into oval patties 1-inch thick. Brown in butter on both sides in a skillet.
Mix the soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over the patties and simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt shortening and add flour.
Let brown until very dark but not burned color.
Set aside and add tomato sauce and water, then add all the cut up vegetables, tomatoes and spices.
Let simmer about 45 minutes or until all the vegetables are done, then bring to a boil and add shrimp.
Cook for about 15 minutes longer. Serve over rice.

title: easy dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Can be served with veggies or chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and dry broccoli.
Cut into small flowerets; also cut stem into small bite size pieces.
Place broccoli and all other ingredients into small bowl. Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 or 2 hours and serve.

title: jalapeno and cheese bread or rolls
directions: In a
very large bowl, combine 2 1/3 cups of the flour, cheese, jalapeno
peppers, 7 teaspoons sugar and the salt; mix well.
In another bowl, combine the water, yeast and remaining 1 teaspoon
sugar.
Let
stand
about 8 minutes;
stir to dissolve all
yeast
granules.
Add
oil
to
the liquid mixture, stirring well.
Then
pour
half
of the liquid mixture in the flour mixture.
With
a wooden spoon, stir to moisten flour as much as possible,
then
add remaining liquid mixture and mix until
flour is
thoroughly
incorporated.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together and chill.
Shape as desired and roll in chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken breast until tender.
Remove any bone or skin. Keep broth; drain vegetables.
Mix with broth, cans of soup.
Add 1 1/2 cans of broth (use empty can).
Chop chicken and line 1 1/2 or 2-quart size casserole dish.
Pour vegetables over chicken. Mix the top crust and drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tom and jerry
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add cinnamon, soda and vanilla; fold in beaten egg whites to which sugar has been slowly added.
For a hearty warm beverage on a cold winter night, set out Tom and Jerry mug.
Add 2 tablespoons of batter, 1 jigger of brandy and 1 teaspoon of rum.
Fill with hot water; stir and sip!

title: cinnamon-applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and candies in 3 cups of boiling water.
Stir in applesauce, lemon juice and salt.
Chill until partially set. Add walnuts.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar until light and fluffy. Add flour mixed to a paste with
a
little of the milk. Stir in the rest of the milk, lemon, juice, rind and salt.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Put in unbaked 9-inch pie crust and bake for 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix and chill overnight. Remove from refrigerator and shape into strawberries, then roll strawberries in red sugar. Stick the stem end of the berry in green sugar. Keep in refrigerator. They will freeze well.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook until firm.
Fill shells, then bake at 375°.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Beat cheese until creamy.
Beat in eggs, milk and pepper. Stir in spinach, ham and onion.
Pour into pie crust; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk together, pour into oblong pan. Blend all other ingredients with juice and milk. Smooth, sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze before serving remove salad from freezer for at least 10 min.

title: dieter's tuna casserole(for 1)
directions: Melt cheese in milk in saucepan. Add 1 slice of bread, crumbled, and thicken. Add tuna.
Place in small uncovered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave for 7 minutes.
Serves 1.

title: cherry coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour pie filling into crust.
Beat together egg and milk.
Add sugar, flour and remaining ingredients except coconut.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in coconut.
Pour over pie filling.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until puffed and browned. Cool before serving.

title: libby's pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs stir in pumpkin and spices, gradually stir in milk. Fill crust with 4 cups each.
Bake at 425 degrees for 15 minutes Reduce to 350 bake 40-50 minutes.
Till silver knife comes out clean when testing.

title: tasty baked irish potatoes
directions: Amounts of ingredients depend on the number of potatoes you will be preparing.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Melt margarine and let cool.
Cook milk, egg and sugar.
Mix crackers crumbs, nuts, coconut and cooked mixture together and spread on cookie sheet lined with graham crackers.
Put layer of crackers on this and add icing on top of crackers.
Cool and cut into squares.
Look for Icing recipe.

title: spinach rice casserole
directions: Cook spinach until tender; drain.
Combine all ingredients. Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Block party surprise!

title: jet rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar, butter and salt together.
Then add yeast to flour and mix everything.
Place in mixing bowl.
Cover with a towel and let rise in a warm place.
Then place dough on floured board and cut out rolls with a biscuit cutter or by hand.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Season to taste.
Cook together in casserole dish.
Add potatoes 1/2 hour before done.
Green beans added just to warm up.

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: mrs. humphries tea
directions: Mix the tea and juice together; sweeten to taste.
Chill and serve world's greatest tea.

title: double pumpkin pies
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs until well beaten. Add the brown sugar and blend well. In a separate bowl, sift together the sugar, flour, nutmeg and pumpkin pie spice, so the spices won't by lumpy. Add the sugar and spices to the egg mixture. Blend the mixture into the pumpkin. Add the milk and salt. Turn the filling into the pie shells. Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes; reduce the heat to 300° and bake until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Very good.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease Bundt or tube pan.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom.
Place frozen rolls in pan in 2 staggered rows.
Sprinkle on brown sugar. Sprinkle on pudding mix.
Sprinkle on dash of cinnamon all over. Cover with wax paper overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Invert quickly on serving plate.
Rolls pull apart as being served. Always a favorite for breakfast!

title: saltine cracker cake
directions: Mix well and spread on cake.

title: angel nut pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar and baking powder slowly to beaten eggs.
Crush crackers and add to mixture with nuts and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased or buttered pie pan and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Spread Cool Whip over pie and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Recipe can be doubled and baked in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: italian olive salad
directions: Pit olives if not already pitted.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Did not give measurements for some ingredients because should suit your taste.
Cauliflower should just be steamed until crispy, not cooked.

title: cinnamon butter cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs; beat until creamy.
Add flour.
Chill.
Roll into balls, then roll balls in a mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and 3 tablespoons cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until light brown, about 8 minutes.

title: stir fried veggies #2
directions: *Use fresh veggies, such as carrots, broccoli, cauliflower, potatoes, yams, corn on the cob, asparagus, green beans, celery, turnips, chard, spinach, etc.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop squash and onion.
Cook together in electric skillet. Stir in all ingredients.
Simmer until mixed well.
Add bread crumbs to thicken.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with butter. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: blackened seasoning mix
directions: Adjust seasonings to taste and double the batch if you have more than 2 good-sized steaks.
Store unused seasonings in a plastic container in the refrigerator.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until brown on top and around edges.

title: pasta and shrimp
directions: Saute garlic in margarine. Add shrimp, half and half, pea pods, red pepper, wine and red pepper flakes. Simmer 3 to 5 minutes, until shrimp are pink. Pour sauce over linguine and toss with 3/4 cup cheese. Serve with remaining cheese. Substitute 1 1/2 cups cooked chicken. Serves 4.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bones.
Break into small chunks.
Mix together the rest of ingredients.
Pour into a frozen pie shell.
Place pats of margarine on top and add top crust.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown.

title: ham and scalloped potato casserole
directions: Place half of the potatoes in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with half of the butter.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour half of mixture over potatoes in dish.
Repeat using remaining potatoes, butter and sauce.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.

title: spicy aspargus
directions: Cook asparagus following directions on box; drain.
Place on platter.
Drizzle French dressing over asparagus.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Add milk, oil and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix together brown sugar and cocoa; sprinkle over batter. Pour hot water over entire batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 of the pecans.
Form a ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Chill.
Serve at room temperature.

title: chicken with brandy
directions: Bone and skin breasts of chicken.
Dust with salt, pepper, thyme and flour.
Melt 1/4 pound butter in frying pan, enough for 4 pieces.
Cook until golden brown, 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove from fire. Pour 1 scant jigger brandy over pieces.
Light with match immediately and flame.
Put back on fire.
Add heavy cream and simmer on low for 10 minutes.
Place pieces on hot platter.
Add paprika to sauce and stir.
Pour over meat.
Serve with string beans, mushrooms and rice.

title: sparkling cranberry punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice and lemonade concentrate in large punch bowl.
Just before serving, stir in club soda.
Sherbet may be floated on beverage in punch bowl.
Makes about 20 servings in tall glasses.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and eggs together well.
Add oil, dry ingredients and vanilla.
Add apples, nuts and dates.
Use either Bundt pan or 3 small loaf pans and bake for 1 hour.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt butter in large cake pan.
Spread brown sugar over butter, then place pineapple rings on top.

title: garden squares
directions: Pat both packages of rolls into a lightly greased jelly roll pan.
Bake as directed on package until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and seasonings.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with chopped vegetables.
Last, add crumbled bacon.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: jumbo stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells as directed on package. Cook souffle as directed on package. Cook meat with onions; drain. Season with salt and pepper.

title: low-fat cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press in spring mold pan.
Mix other ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and let sit until cool.
Remove and refrigerate.

title: italian summer vegetables
directions: Set range at low heat.
Pour olive oil into large skillet. Stir in garlic and chopped onion and thinly sliced squash and add to cubed tomatoes.
Add spices and simmer until vegetables are done.
Stir while cooking.
After vegetables are done, sprinkle with cheese and cover to set for about 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Beat sugar and margarine together.
Add egg and coconut flavor.
Mix biscuit mix and potato flakes and blend the mixture into the sugar mixture with a spoon.
Chill dough about 1 hour before shaping.
Using a teaspoon, drop dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Watch carefully, because they brown very quickly.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening (Crisco) and sugar together, then add eggs, beating well.
Add other ingredients; mix well, then pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: rice chicken and cheese
directions: Fry diced onion in margarine until light brown.
Add rice and a little water.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Add chicken and cheese; mix well.
Let stand 5 minutes and enjoy.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Grease 3 or 4 bread pans.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: molasses-glazed ham
directions: Remove skin from ham; place ham, fat side up, on a baking rack.
Score fat in a diamond design and stud with cloves.
Insert meat thermometer, making sure it does not touch fat or bone.
Bake ham at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

Remove ham from oven. Combine remaining ingredients; baste ham with molasses mixture. Return ham to oven and bake an additional 30 to 40 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 140°, basting frequently with glaze.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Make pie crusts as directed on package for two-crust pie using a 9-inch pie pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and stir into dressing.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place a layer of dressing, a layer of chicken and a layer of celery which has been diluted with chicken broth.
Repeat a layer of dressing, a layer of chicken and 1 can cream of chicken soup diluted with chicken broth.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: brazilian rice
directions: Fry onion, garlic and bay leaf in oil until golden brown.
Add chopped tomatoes.
Stir until tomatoes are soft.
Add rice and stir into tomato mixture.
Add enough water to cover rice.
Cover and simmer until moisture is absorbed.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: taco dip(serves a party)
directions: Layer ingredients in order and serve with taco chips and veggies.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, candied cherries and nuts.
Form into 2 rolls, each 2-inches in diameter and 8-inches long.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap and chill several hours or overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or until edges are golden.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: crock pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger onion and pepper. Add sauces and simmer. Cook noodles. Layer in crockpot: ground beef mixture, noodles, cheeses, pepperoni, and mushrooms. Keep layering to top. Warm until cheese melts.

title: strawberries in wine(simple and simply delicious)
directions: Hull the strawberries and slice or cut them into quarters. Mix the wine and the Splenda and pour the mixture over the berries. Add the cinnamon stick and refrigerate, stirring from time to time, for at least 12 hours (but 2 days wouldn't hurt!). Yield: 4 servings.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375° in muffin tins.
Recipe may be cut in half.
Batter will last 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: thai chicken with vegetables
directions: Heat 2 teaspoons of the oil over high heat in a large, nonstick skillet.
Add the lemon grass or lemon peel, garlic, ginger and chilies; cook for 15 seconds.
Add the chicken and green onions; sprinkle with salt.
Cook, stirring until golden, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Transfer to a plate.

title: pasta with scallops, mushrooms and spinach
directions: Anyone who enjoys Chinese style marinades should try this recipe.
Use this with pork loin "quick fry" chops or cubed chicken.
Although the meat can be broiled in an oven, the taste is just not as good as when cooked on a charcoal or gas grill.

title: miniature peanut butter cups
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and both sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour, soda and salt to make a soft dough. Shape dough into 40 balls and place in tassie pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Press peanut butter down into each one and let stand in pan to cool for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Grind all vegetables together in food chopper.
Mix with beef. Season.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream together lard, sugar and egg.
Add persimmon and mix well.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and coconut extract.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together the ingredients with rotary beater.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.
Preheat oven.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter and Crisco until fluffy. Add sugar and mix until creamy. Add eggs, 1 at a time. Add flour and milk alternately. Add dry pudding mix. Mix well.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 275° to 300° for 2 hours. Turn off oven and let cake sit 15 minutes in the oven. Turn cake out on rack to cool.

title: mexican brunch
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Remove seeds from chiles and arrange in single layer in dish.
Sprinkle with tomatoes and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients by hand until smooth.
Pour over top.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All.
Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Place in casserole dish sprayed with vegetable spray.
Crush the roll of Ritz crackers.
Mix cracker crumbs with melted margarine; spread over top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir ground cranberries, sugar, marshmallows and let set out of refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, add apples, peeled and diced, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Dream whip.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in large bowl.
Mash.
Add butter, bourbon, orange juice, brown sugar, salt and spice; beat until fluffy smooth.
Spoon into buttered 6-cup baking dish.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 375° while shredding chicken. Boil chicken in 1 can of enchilada sauce and 3 cups of water. Strain and set aside to cool. Once cooled, shred by hand (or pull apart). Pour 2 cans of enchilada sauce in shallow bowl. Wet tortillas on both sides. Place sour cream, chicken and cheese in the middle and roll. Put in cake pan. When out of chicken, put left over sour cream in sauce bowl and mix. Pour over enchiladas. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts and bubbles a little. Serve with side of refried beans or rice.

title: english pastry
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in greased pie pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: never fail garlic dill pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers lengthwise
or
when
bigger slice them round. Put 2 pieces dill in
quart jar, one on top and one on bottom. Do the same with
the
garlic, 2 pieces per jar.
Mix water, vinegar and salt and
bring to a boil.
Pour hot liquid over pickles
and if
not
enough
liquid,
make
some
more. Process in hot water bath until
it comes to a good boil.
Set aside and leave in 1/2 hour.

title: grosmommy's half-moon pies
directions: Cook apples
in
cups water, covered, until soft and most of the
water
has
been
taken up.
Remove from heat and stir until smooth with potato masher.
Add sugar, cinnamon and salt. Cool.
Mix flour, shortening (heap shortening) and salt well.
Add cold water to make a soft pie dough.

title: beef stew
directions: Place meat in crock-pot with one can of broth and water on high.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Cover.
Prepare
veggies and add to crock-pot.
Cover with more broth or more water.
Add parsley. Cook on high for 4 to 6 hours or 10 to 12 hours on low.

title: chicken-macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients except eggs.
Carefully mix in eggs or save them for garnish, if desired.
Chill before serving.
Calories per serving:
about 270.
Makes 6 servings, about 1 cup each.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time. Add flour, milk and nuts last.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325° in tube pan.

title: wet burritos
directions: Brown hamburger; add seasoning packets.
Add onion to hamburger mix.
Roll up tortillas with meat and remaining ingredients, leaving out 1 cup of cheeses and remaining salsa. Put in a baking pan; top with salsa and cheeses.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: never fail chess pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, cornmeal, salt, butter, cream, and vanilla.
Blend well before pouring into a 10 inch unbaked pie shell.
Baked at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Stir
confectioners sugar, water and vanilla.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt into the scalded
milk.
Stir in yeast, potato and egg.
Gradually add flour
to
make
soft
dough.
Turn onto floured surface. Knead until
soft.
Place
in greased bowl.
Turn so that all sides
are greased.
Cover.
Let
rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Take out
and
roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and let dough rise again.
Then cut doughnuts and drop in 375° oil.

title: ritz cracker salad
directions: Fold in pineapple.
Put on top of crust.
Chill well.

title: stuffed pocket bread
directions: Fry ground beef and drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper for 5 minutes.
Add hamburger, salt, pepper, garlic, chile powder and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Saute for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stuff pocket bread with meat and some of the shredded cheese.
Place in baking dish.
After all pockets are stuffed, pour remaining cheese over top and cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes. Serve with 2 slices of cucumbers and sour cream on top of each pocket.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour the cup of water over yeast. Add 1 teaspoon sugar. Stir. Let stand 10 minutes. Scald the milk and dissolve in it the salt and sugar. Let cool. When milk is lukewarm, add it to the softened yeast. Blend yeast mixture with about half the flour and beat smooth. Add beaten eggs and shortening, softened but not hot. Add enough more flour to make dough somewhat softer than for bread. Knead smooth. If desired, store dough immediately in refrigerator after placing it in a greased vessel covered with double thickness of wax paper tied down securely. If preferred, let the dough when first mixed rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk. Knead down, then store in refrigerator about 2 hours. Before rolls are wanted, take as much dough as required. Shape and place in greased pan. Let rise in warm place or over warm water until doubled. Bake about 15 minutes at 450°. This dough will keep for a week in the refrigerator.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix well and let dry.

title: coconut-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, butter, egg and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and coconut.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: scalloped clams
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until liquid is cooked up.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients (the first 5 ingredients).
Mix into dry ingredients the mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Blend well for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Test with a toothpick in the center of the cake to be sure if it's done.

title: italian beef
directions: Roast the meat for approximately 1 to 2 hours (depending on the size of the roast). Slice roast in very thin slices.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and add to the water already in pan after it has roasted for 1 to 2 hours.
Add meat back into pan and cook for approximately another 45 minutes.
Serve warm with hard rolls.
You may want to add hot peppers (or mild pepper) to your sandwich.

title: mediterranean pasta toss
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package.
Meanwhile, cook and stir peppers, onion and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Toss with pasta.
Serve hot.

title: easy broccoli quiche
directions: Mix broccoli, onion and mushrooms with a little oil in a buttered pie plate. Mix together milk, egg, cheese, biscuit mix, salt and pepper and pour over broccoli mixture. Bake at 375° for 25-30 minutes or until firm.

title: festive sausage cups
directions: On a lightly floured surface, roll pastry to 1/8 inch thickness. Cut with a 2 1/2 inch round cookie cutter. Press onto the bottom and up the sides of greased miniature muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 6-8 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from pans to cool on wire racks. In a skillet, brown sausage; drain well and set aside. In the same skillet, saute onions in butter until tender. Add mushrooms, sliced olives, salt and pepper. Sprinkle with flour. Add cream; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Stir in sausage. Reduce heat; simmer until thickened, about 5-10 minutes, stirring constantly. Spoon into pastry cups; sprinkle with cheese. Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Garnish with chopped olives.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Place hen in a large Dutch oven and cover with water.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer until tender.
Remove hen from broth, reserving broth.
Cool hen; remove meat from bones.
Dice meat.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients in large pan until tender.
Cook 20 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: luscious lasagna
directions: Spray 11 x 13-inch pan.
Layer noodles, uncooked sausage, cheeses and vegetables.
Repeat layers; pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour, covered.

title: almond cherry frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and mix until smooth; don't add cherries until all mixed well.
Make enough for filling and sides and top of 2 layer cake.

title: italian redfish
directions: Coat saucepan with half and half cream.
Add a little salt, 1/8 stick of butter and a little garlic powder and place on a very, very low fire.
Bake redfish in microwave or oven until done.
When redfish is almost finished, place a large slice of Mozzarella cheese over every piece of fish and replace it until the cheese starts to melt.
As fish is about ready, raise fire under sauce a little.
Add Parmesan cheese until creamy.
When fish and sauce is ready, pour sauce over the fish.
Add parsley for decoration.
Enjoy!

title: mother's spanish rice
directions: Cut bacon
strips into 1/4 inch pieces. Brown in the frying pan. Pour off all but 2 Tbsp. grease. Dice onions and add to bacon and brown. Dice green pepper after parboiling
(just bring to a boil and drain). Add to bacon and onion while cooking.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook noodles until tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add cottage cheese, sour cream, salt, vanilla, eggs and raisins.
Stir in cooked noodles.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until golden brown.

title: taco party dip
directions: Beat taco mix, cream cheese and sour cream on high until smooth.
Spread on platter 1/2-inch thick.
Cover with lettuce and tomatoes, then cheese.
Serve with chips.
Enjoy!

title: coconut macaroons
directions: In medium size bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon about 1 inch apart onto well-greased sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from sheet immediately and let cool.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cinnamon-apple dutch baby
directions: In a 10 or 12-inch frying pan with ovenproof handle, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Stir in cinnamon and sugar.
Thinly slice apples into pan. Cook, stirring until apples are translucent, about 5 minutes.
Place pan, uncovered, in a 425° oven while you mix the batter, about 5 minutes.
In a blender or food processor, whirl eggs and flour until smooth.
Blend in milk. (Or whisk eggs with flour, then add milk.)
Pour batter over apples in pan. Bake, uncovered, until pancake is puffy and golden, about 15 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar and let stand about 5 minutes. Cut into wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp mandarin salad
directions: Have shrimp and mandarin segments chilled in the cans.
Drain. Rinse shrimp in cold water; blot dry.
Soften sour cream with dressing; combine with shrimp, fruit, celery, onion and cashews. Serve on shredded lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: basic foolproof pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt and shortening into coarse crumbs.
Mix vinegar, beaten egg and ice water together; add to flour mixture. Add more water if necessary to work into soft dough ball. Refrigerate 30 minutes to let dough rest.
Press into pie plate.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: In large pot, melt margarine. Add chopped onions and cook until tender. Stir in soup and milk, mixing well. Add spices and turkey meat and bring to a slow boil.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Devein and
wash shrimp thoroughly and drain.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper
and
curry, mix well.
Sprinkle with flour, brown lightly in	frypan	on
medium
heat.
Place
shrimp
in baking dish.
Arrange
slices of bell pepper, onions and bacon strips over shrimp
and
sprinkle	with
chopped celery.
Pour sauce over dish content and bake for about 1/2 hour.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Prepare the mushroom by wiping them with a damp cloth, removing all dirt or grit that might be on them.
Gently twist the stems and remove.
Combine the cream cheese, crab meat, and seasoning in a mixing bowl and beat until well blended.
Fill each mushroom cap and then dip the top into a combined mixture of crumbs and Parmesan.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil for 1 to 2 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown.

title: christmas holly wreaths
directions: Mix on medium-high heat the butter and marshmallows until melted.
Turn off heat; add food coloring until desired darkness. Add corn flakes.
Stir until all are coated.
Pinch off small amounts with buttered hands; make small wreaths.
Place red hots for berries.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix bread crumbs with milk in bowl. Add ground beef and salt. Mix well. Shape into balls. Put in baking dish. Mix well the remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls. Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes until done.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain well.
Cook potatoes and cream and prepare them as you would mashed potatoes.
Drain string beans.
Pour hamburger meat into oblong casserole dish. Pour string beans on top of meat.
Spread potatoes on top of string beans.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned.

title: brownies
directions: Beat first six ingredients together well; add flour and nuts, mix well.
Bake in large pan 25 minutes at 350°.
I use jelly roll pan (10 1/2 x 16-inch).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add pecans; stir.
Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture; stir well.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool 10 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: tyler's peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press lightly.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Let cool 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown chicken, onion. Mix in cream cheese.

title: m&m party cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, slowly mix in flour and about half the M&M's.
Drop by the spoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Top with M&M's and bake for 3 to 5 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: fast n fancy macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients mixing well.
Drop by teaspoons 1 inch apart on well greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove at once using moistened spatula.

title: puff rice balls
directions: Mix together corn syrup, molasses, brown sugar and vinegar. Boil to brittle stage, then add butter and salt.
Allow bubbling to stop.
Quickly stir in puff rice cereal.
Butter your hands and form balls.
Let stand on wax paper until cold.

title: baked ham loaf
directions: Mix together well, bake at 350° to 400° in loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: "goopy" hot dish
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, with a tight fitting cover, lightly brown beef and onion.
Season to taste.
Turn heat down to simmer. Spread Minute rice over beef.
Pour and spread undrained corn, then pour tomato sauce over the corn.
Add green olives.
Cover tightly and let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Just before serving, add cheese slices and cover for 2 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add pineapple syrup, lemon juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add pineapple, cranberries, orange, celery and nuts.
Pour in dish.
Chill until set.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of boiling water.
Chill until it starts to thicken.
Fold in mayonnaise, milk, pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts.
Congeal and serve.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: french onion soup
directions: Preheat broiler.
Butter both sides of bread.
Arrange on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Cut into squares and set aside.
Slice onions thinly.
Melt butter in large skillet and add onions.
Saute over medium heat about 15 minutes or until onions turn light golden color.
Heat broth in saucepan.
Add sauteed onions.
Season with salt to taste.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together and spoon into pie crust. Chill.

title: chocolate snack cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat water and butter until butter is melted.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to the egg mixture. Beat for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Serve plain or with vanilla ice cream and chocolate syrup drizzled on top.

title: mandarin orange spinach salad
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Toast almonds until light gold in color.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Wash broccoli and cut off flowerets into bite-size pieces.
In a large bowl, combine spinach, broccoli, onions and cooled almond slices.
Lightly toss. Add Mandarin oranges and 1/4 cup Honey-Orange Vinaigrette Dressing and lightly toss again.
Add more dressing if needed. Serve as a side salad or add grilled or fried chicken tenderloins for a meal.

title: hawaii wedding cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box

title: turkey meatballs(crock-pot)
directions: Mix all, except soup and wine.
Form into balls.
Coat balls with whole wheat (or white) flour.
Place balls in crock-pot (I use a small one).
Cover with mixture of soup and wine (I use a semi-dry red).
Serve over noodles, bread or whatever.

title: pork chops california
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Place slice of lemon on each chop.
Combine brown sugar, ketchup and water.
Pour over chops.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Remove cover.
Simmer 10 minutes, basting chops occasionally.

title: creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except last two in a pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes. Blend butter with flour, add to the corn.
Mix well and remove from heat. Put finished corn in heat proof casserole.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and place under a broiler till evenly browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: "cajun" black beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in enough water to cover.
Cube ham.
Chop onion and pepper.
Braise pepper, onion and ham in small amount of corn oil.
Place beans in cooker and cover with water, seasoning and the braised mixture of ham, onion and pepper.
Cook until beans are tender.

title: cheese bread
directions: Place French bread on foil on cookie sheet.
Slice on angle, not all the way through.
Stuff slices with cheese.
In saucepan, simmer together remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Seal foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: karen's chicken pot pie
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish.
Press pie crust to conform to bottom of casserole dish.
Break chicken into small pieces and place on crust.
Mix soup with broth from chicken (as much broth as you need to get soupy consistency).
Add peas and potatoes to mixture; pour over chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Take crescent rolls out of cans and slice roll into 1 inch strips.
Unroll strips and place in a criss-cross pattern over pie filling.
Bake at 350 to 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cover lightly with foil if needed.

title: campfire hash
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil. Saute onion and garlic until tender. Add potatoes. Cook uncovered, over medium heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add sausage; cook and stir until potatoes are tender and well browned. Stir in chilies and corn; cook until thoroughly heated.

title: sweet potato dump cake
directions: Grease your DEEP cooking dish and add some flour to coat the grease. Discard all leftover flour. Cover bottom and sides with pie crust. Add a couple layers of tater slices, layer of butter and cover with brown sugar, then a light dusting of cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger. Cut 1 pie crust into strips and add a few to the top of that layer. Continue layers until the dish is full (or you run out of taters). Cover final layer with last pie crust. Add thin slices of butter and light coat of brown sugar to top of crust.

title: skillet barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Drain excess oil.
Put remaining ingredients over chops and cover.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, until chops are tender.
Use the sauce over rice or potatoes.
It's delicious!
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: bacon corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove, saving 2 to 3 tablespoons fat. Add onion and green pepper and fry.
Stir in corn and heat.
Serve sprinkled with bacon.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Wash and cut up.
Cook together until done.
Scoop into blender (whip) and then put in a large boiler and add paprika, salt, black pepper, garlic salt, sugar, tomato paste and spices. Slow boil about 2 1/2 hours.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: heavenly white cake
directions: Follow directions for mixing cake, using 3 egg whites.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake.
After cake has cooled, punch holes in top of cake and pour can of cream of coconut over top.
Then pour can of sweetened condensed milk over top of cake. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Spread nondairy topping evenly over cake.
Sprinkle on coconut flakes.
Cover with cling wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Place grated cheese in bottom of greased casserole.
Add sliced potatoes on top of cheese.
Pour soup and water on top of potatoes.
Bake in 400° oven until potatoes are done (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Cover to cook.

title: egg in a nest
directions: Butter bread on both sides.
Cut a hole in the center of the bread large enough to fit an egg.
Put buttered bread in a skillet and break an egg in hole of bread; take the hole of the bread and put it in skillet on the side to toast.
Cook on low heat and flip over to cook on both sides until egg is done.
Cut bread around egg in pie shapes and use to dip in egg.

title: banana nuggets(cookies)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender.
Add eggs, bananas, oatmeal, chips or raisins.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 48.

title: grape jelly
directions: Place grapes and sugar in saucepan; add no water.
Boil 20 minutes or more real fast.
Remove from heat.
Work through sieve or Foly food mill.
Pour in glasses.
Seven cups equals 3 pounds sugar, 6 cups equals 3 pounds grapes.

title: peach cake
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pies
directions: Mix together chicken, 1 cup cheese, vegetables, onion, 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup and 1/4 can cream of chicken soup. Separate crescent rolls.
Press 2 crescent rolls together to form a rectangular shape.
Scoop chicken mixture onto each rectangle (4).
Fold rolls around mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Cover with sauce.

title: pilaf
directions: Saute onions and drained mushrooms in saucepan with butter. Pour rice and consomme in 2-quart casserole.
Add sauteed ingredients, salt, pepper and herb seasoning.
Bake (covered) for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together in large boiler.
Gradually stir in the milk, then heat to boiling.
Boil for about 1 minute (to a good rolling boil).
Then remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Let sit until butter is almost melted.
Then stir until it starts to get thickened.
At this time, stir in oatmeal, 1 cup at a time.
Pour in buttered 7 1/2 x 12-inch pan and let cool before cutting into squares.

title: vegetable goodies
directions: Cook beans, drain.
Put into bowl with mushrooms, onions and salad dressing.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Toss to marinate occasionally.
Cut tops from tomatoes.
Scoop out centers and drain.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fill with bean mixture. Refrigerate until serving time (4 servings).

title: talerine
directions: Brown beef in skillet, add rotel, can of water, noodles, bring to boil.
Cover and lower heat to simmer until noodles are ready.
Add corn and chili powder.
Pour into 9 x 13 glass pan, top with cheese.
Cook 350 until bubbly, serve with yellow cornbread.

title: vegetable bread appetizer
directions: Roll crescent rolls out flat onto cookie sheets.
Bake to package directions (be sure not to overcook; lightly brown).
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and powdered dressing mix; spread over cooled rolls.
Put on the vegetables of your choice; top with grated cheese.
Cut into bite size pieces and serve.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Thoroughly combine eggs, sugar, butter or oleo, lemon juice and vanilla; stir in coconut.
Pour filling into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool before serving.
If desired, garnish with whipped cream and toasted coconut.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine in saucepan the Jell-O and pineapple.
Heat until dissolved.
Let cool, then add the buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: white chili
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil until translucent (no color).
Add spices, turkey, beans and chicken stock.
Simmer for 1/2 hour and stir in 2/3 of cheese.
If desired, garnish with sour cream and jalapenos.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Melt chips and margarine slowly in boiler.
When melted, take from heat and add noodles and peanuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.
When cold, can wrap in foil.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Slice tomatoes
3/8-inch thick; set aside and let water drain. Salt and
pepper
to taste.
Turn in meal.
Fry in hot grease in skillet.

title: beer soup(bier suppe)
directions: In a 4-quart kettle, pour a bottle of beer and an equal amount of cold water and a pinch of salt.	Use the beer bottle as a measure.
In another kettle, pour milk plus water.	Bring both to boiling point, but do not boil.
Add beaten egg to the milk.
Now pour the contents
from
one kettle to the other, 6 or 8 times to prevent curdling.

title: fruit and pudding
directions: Drain all canned fruits and add whatever additions of fresh fruit in large bowl.
Mix together pudding mixture and pour over fruit and combine.

title: cheese strata
directions: Butter bread and cut into cubes.
Make alternate layers of bread cubes and cheese in buttered casserole dish.
Blend rest of ingredients in bowl and pour over bread and cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap, refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snowball salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix Cool Whip, sour cream and sugar thoroughly.
Add pineapple, bananas and lemon juice.
Add pecans and cherries.
Keep covered in refrigerator or freezer.
This will serve 20 people.
Will keep from Thanksgiving until Christmas.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Bake in 375 degree oven for an hour.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook until vegetables are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes. Blend flour to half of the milk. Add rest of milk. Add to vegetables. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Add grated cheese and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: individual quiches
directions: Roll out pastry.
Cut twelve 4-inch circles.
Fit into muffin cups. Fill each with some shrimp, onion and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients.
Pour over cheese. Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all salad ingredients.
Add enough dressing to lightly coat or hold salad ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: cherry fancy
directions: Cream the brown sugar with the butter in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add flour, pumpkin pie spice, soda and egg; blend well.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar and mix in other ingredients.
Add chocolate syrup as you desire.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: cream corn custard
directions: Stir corn, eggs, cheese and green pepper together.
Combine flour, sugar and seasonings.
Add to corn mixture.
Stir in half and half.
Spoon into a greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Set baking dish in a deep pan and add one inch hot water to outer pan. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, salt, soda and sour cream.
Set aside. Cook until boiling point is reached and well blended the margarine, water and cocoa.
Add to flour mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost while hot.

title: applesauce stack cake
directions: Heat filling ingredients in saucepan.
Spread about 1/2 cup of filling on first layer; add a layer of cake, then filling, repeating for all layers and ending with the last of the applesauce mixture on top.
Chill until ready to eat.
Best after in refrigerator for a few days.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar together; pour over drained sauerkraut. Add celery, onion, green pepper and celery seed.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Keeps well.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Place 1/4 cup
sugar
in
skillet
and	melt,
stirring constantly until light
brown syrup forms.	Gradually add milk and blend well.
Add
remaining
2 cups sugar and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove
from heat; add butter and vanilla.	Cool. Pour in buttered pan.
Cut in squares and top with pecans.

title: old fashioned custard pie
directions: Beat eggs or egg yolks slightly with rotary beater.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake for about 40 minutes, or until silver knife inserted into side of filling comes out clean (center is soft but will set later).
Bake in a hot oven for the first 15 minutes; finish in a 350° oven for remaining time.

title: homemade orange refresher
directions: Combine the first five ingredients in a blender container and process at high speed.
Add ice cubes, a few at a time, blending until slushy.
Garnish with orange slices, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Use bread that is dry, break in pieces.
Add salt, pepper and sage.
Put in celery and onion.
Pour eggs and margarine over this.
Use just enough chicken broth to make a moist dressing. This can be used all at once or wrap in foil and freeze.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan (add vinegar last). Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in ingredients in order.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Optional items, such as chocolate chips, M&M's, etc. may be added prior to baking.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Heat milk, cheese and soup.
Add hash browns and sausage.
Put in casserole dish and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: delicious oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheets with vegetable cooking spray.
In a large mixer bowl, combine oats, oat bran, flour, cocoa powder, baking soda and sugar.
In a cup, combine peanut butter, milk and vanilla.
Stir into dry mixture, thoroughly combine.
Add apples and dates.
Batter will be stiff. Drop by tablespoons onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread, milk, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Make into balls.
Pour ketchup, diced onion and vinegar over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb-ginger jam
directions: Boil 1/2 hour, then can or freeze.

title: creamy refrigerator dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts together.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, until brown.
Cool.

title: baptist cookies
directions: Pour in bowl and mix, then pour into iron skillet and stir cooking on low heat until dates are melted or dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Put 2 1/2 cups Rice Krispies in bowl and pour mixture over them with 3/4 cup pecans and mix.
Let cool, then shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Dice ingredients with each of 1/3 mixture. Put into utility dish and dot with butter. Put enough in so mixture will be coated with liquid.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for about one hour at 350°.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Cook together until vegetables are done.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and boil until thick.
Use on hot dogs, chicken, etc.

title: penguin salad
directions: Cut a thin slice off large end of egg and stand egg up.
For penguin's head, insert one end of toothpick lengthwise into a ripe olive.
Insert other end in top of egg.
Use 1/4 of olive (cut lengthwise) for each wing or lengthwise sliver for "necktie"; poke short piece of toothpick into each section of olive first (from inner side), then into egg.
For feet, cut a lengthwise slice of carrot, a little less than 1/2 inch thick.
Cut the slice crosswise in 3/4-inch lengths.
Taper sides of each piece of carrot and notch wide end to make webbed foot.
Tuck a pair of feet part way under egg.
Whittle a beak from carrot and push into olive-head for nose. Place on lettuce.

title: mini-pizzas
directions: Flatten biscuits to 1/4 inch thick.
Place biscuits on cookie sheet.
Cover with spaghetti sauce (use homemade or bottled).
Add cheese on top, then put pepperonies on and bake in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Can be stored in plastic Baggies and microwaved when desired.

title: chocolate pie 1
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, salt, egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Cook in double boiler until thickened, not too much. Bake pie shells some to set.
Add mixture. Pour into two pie shells and bake at 350° until set.
Cool and cover with meringue. Cook until browned well.

title: carol's homemade chicken soup
directions: Combine all in pot and cook until egg noodles are done.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Put beans in a big pot.
Add all remaining ingredients to the beans.
Let cook for 1 hour on low heat.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, put on plate and dust with powdered sugar.

title: best strawberry jam
directions: Heat strawberries and sure jell. Stir well. Cool and refrigerate overnight. Next day add white sugar and karo syrup. Stir very well. Refrigerate.

title: fettuccine compolle
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cut chicken in small pieces and dip in flour, then fry in butter.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add cheese to heavy cream and cook on low heat until mixed well.
Add cooked noodles, chicken and cooked peas to the cheese and milk.

title: easy mexican rice
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add rice; stir for a minute or two until slightly golden.
Reduce heat; add Ro-Tel tomatoes, juice and water.
Stir well; cover and cook for about 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Salt, pepper and batter pork chops (center cut).
Fry chops and drain.
Place rings of bell pepper 1/4 inch thick over chops.
In each ring, place 1 tablespoon of washed, uncooked rice.
Layer 1/4 inch raw potatoes, then a layer of onions.
Pour tomatoes over this.
If everything is not covered, add a little water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until potatoes and onions are done. Makes a full course meal.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add fruit and nuts and Crisco and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until it shrinks from side of pan.
Serve with whipped cream or ice with favorite vanilla icing.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large pot, bring rice and water to a simmer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer; stir often to prevent sticking.
Add more water or tomato juice, if needed, while cooking.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes or until rice, peppers and onions are tender.

title: lemonade cake with lemon glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend well, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Thoroughly prick warm cake with a utility fork completely thoroughy to bottom of cake.
Gradually spoon glaze over cake until completely absorbed.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Mix all other ingredients in with Jell-O.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: buffalo shrimp
directions: Boil shrimp, peel, devein and butterfly.
Dip into light batter and fry.
Shake in Durkee's hot sauce.
Place on plate.

title: french rhubarb pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and add to rhubarb; stir until well coated.
Pour into pie shell.

title: caesar salad
directions: Process all but Parmesan, croutons and lettuce in food processor until well blended.
Put dressing in a bowl.
Rinse, dry and tear romaine lettuce into bite size pieces.
Add lettuce to salad bowl.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: In a saucepan, mix the first 6 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Heat cream in top of a double boiler over simmering water; add to the tomato mixture just before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients except dried mustard and lemon juice.
Put mustard in lemon juice; then add to first mixture.
Stick fork several times in flank steak and submerge in marinade, turning occasionally, for 6 hours or overnight.
Grill steak as desired. Marinade can be frozen and reused.

title: cheese soup
directions: Chop cabbage, onion, celery, carrots and potatoes.
Add to broth; cook until tender.
Turn down heat.
Add cheese and chicken; heat thoroughly, but do not boil, or cheese will curdle. Use a large soup pot.

title: easy crock-pot roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Lay in crock-pot.
Mix onion soup and mushroom soup.
Pour over roast.
Cook until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: dad's homemade ice cream
directions: Need ice cream maker for recipe.

title: draw punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in warm water in a pan and cool.
Add other ingredients; mix well and serve over ice.

title: wacky cake
directions: Melt butter; pour into dry ingredients.
Add vinegar, vanilla and water; mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour hot water over 1/2 cup sugar, salt and margarine; stir to lukewarm.
Put yeast and 2 teaspoons sugar in 1 cup warm water, set 10 minutes.
Beat eggs.
Mix liquid ingredients.
Add 4 cups flour and stir smooth.
Add 3 1/2 cups flour, not too stiff.
Put dough in refrigerator.
Use next day or for a week as wanted.
Bake at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart round casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix and let
stand overnight or longer.
(Good to serve with stroganoff.)

title: shrimp vegetable dip
directions: Let chill for 1 to 2 hours (it tastes better).
Cut up your favorite dipping vegetables, cauliflower, carrots, celery, broccoli and cucumber are all tasty.

title: brandy slush
directions: Bring 7 cups of water and the sugar to a boil. Cool. Put all tea bags into 2 cups boiling water. Cool. Combine all ingredients; mix well and freeze.

title: quick n' easy corn relish
directions: In a bowl, combine drained corn and cooking oil.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, minced onion, salt and celery seed.
Cover and bring to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Add to corn mixture, cover and cool.
Refrigerate several hours or until thoroughly chilled.
Drain to serve.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: crescent herb swirl(hearty herb loaf tastes homemade)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into two long rectangles. Slightly overlap long sides to form 12 x 7-inch rectangle; firmly press perforations and edges to seal.
Combine margarine, parsley, oregano, dill and garlic powder.
Spread about 1 1/2 tablespoons of the herb butter evenly over dough.
Reserve remaining mixture.

title: chicken nibbles
directions: Combine all ingredients except wings and mix well.

Place wings, skin side down, in shallow baking dish. Cover with 1/3 of the sauce. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, brushing occasionally with remaining sauce. Turn wings and brush with sauce. Bake about 10 minutes longer or until tender.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly first 5 ingredients.
In second bowl, mix next 4 ingredients.
Add to flour mixture next 2 ingredients.
Add flour-cereal mixture to first mixture.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet quickly.

title: chimichangas
directions: Combine the meat with the onion soup and green chilies in a slow cooker.
Cook for 8 hours over a low heat.
When it is done, the stew meat will fall apart into tender pieces when stirred.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crumble meat into 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes or until meat loses pink color when stirred.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix and water.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir in chips and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes or until thoroughly heated; stir.
Top with tomatoes and remaining cheese. Microwave 2 minutes or until cheese is melted, turning dish after 1 minute.
Top with sour cream.
Serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and place in large bowl with a lid. Mix together the cinnamon and sugar.
Pour mixed sugar and cinnamon over biscuits and shake well.
Melt butter and set aside. Take sugared biscuit pieces and empty into a Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Pour butter over top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Pecans or other nuts are optional; place at bottom of pan before adding biscuit pieces.

title: apple crumb pie(microwave)
directions: Melt butter on High 1 minute in a glass mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar and crumbs; mix well.
Press firmly half of mixture to line a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Place apple slices piled high in crumb-lined pie plate and sprinkle with sugar mixed with cinnamon.

title: christmas candy
directions: Boil sugars, cream and butter to soft ball stage.
Add dates and cook 5 to 8 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add coconut, nuts, vanilla and cream of tartar.
Stir enough to blend well.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut when cool. Candy is best if packed in a container and left to age for a week or so.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar until well blended. Add egg and mix well. Set aside.

title: skillet zucchini lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese and egg; set aside.
Brown zucchini in butter.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Layer zucchini, beef, sauce and cheese mixture.
Top with Mozzarella.
Cover and cook over medium-low for 15 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings, 320 calories per serving.

title: raisin, peanut and carrot sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on buttered bread, bun or toast.
May be kept in a covered container in the refrigerator for a few days.

title: corn by rose
directions: Cook and drain corn.
Cook together the next 4 ingredients until melted.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese (crushed corn flakes can be substituted).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetarian casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat oil; add onion and garlic.
Saute until onion is softened.
Add zucchini and cook, stirring constantly, until tender-crisp, about 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, beans and seasonings; bring to a boil. Transfer bean mixture to shallow 1-quart flameproof casserole; sprinkle with cheese and bake until thoroughly heated, 20 to 25 minutes.
Place under broiler until cheese is browned.
Serves 2.

title: diet fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put artificial sweetener in orange juice; pour over cranberries.
Let set 1 hour.
Combine raisins, pecans, cranberries, pineapple chunks, orange rind and lemon rind. Add melted margarine.
Sift and measure flour. Add salt, soda and spices to flour and sift.
Put in muffin cups and bake 35 minutes.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix all together and put in refrigerator, covered.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and broccoli separately. After cooking, place chicken and broccoli in buttered casserole dish. Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Spread over chicken and broccoli. Place cheese about middle of the casserole. Place crumbs on top of cheese. Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: white peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Cook in 4-quart pressure cooker on high. Turn down to medium-high.
Test in cool water until forms soft ball.
Beat until thick enough.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cut when cool.

title: layered vegetable casserole
directions: Arrange carrots, celery, green pepper and beans in layers in buttered casserole dish.
Combine tomatoes, tapioca, sugar and seasonings in a saucepan.
Heat.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and top with melted butter.
Return to oven and bake, uncovered, about 1 hour.
Serves 15.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; drain.
Debone.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix chicken, sour cream, soup and carrots; mix well; set aside.

title: hot pepperoni dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute pecans in butter.
Combine the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with the pecans.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Spread on snack crackers.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; form in small balls.
Make indentations with thumb.
Bake at 375° until the bottom of the cookie is brown but the top is still white.

title: sugar and spice nuts
directions: Prepare the same way.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine tomato sauce, salt, pepper, eggs, crackers and onions.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Add ground beef.
Mix gently but thoroughly.
Put mixture in a microwavable Bundt pan.
(Or form mixture into a 9-inch ring on microwave-safe baking dish.)
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High power for 5 minutes.
Pour off any juices.
Microwave, covered, at Medium power for about 10 minutes.
Remove wax paper and spread ketchup on top. Microwave at High power for about 5 minutes or until done.

title: heavenly cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: butter roll
directions: Mix together with mixer until well blended.
Pour over crust. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 20 minutes before serving.
Is wonderful with a scoop of vanilla ice cream, it helps cut the sweetness.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Chop onion and saute in butter.
Mix Cheez Whiz with butter and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna mold
directions: Heat cream cheese and cream of mushroom soup.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water and add to heated mixture.
Add celery, onion, garlic powder and parsley flakes.
Pour over tuna that has been crumbled.
Mix and pour into mold.
Chill well.

title: pecan pies
directions: Divide and make 2 pies.
Place pecan halves on top before baking.

title: broccoli rice casserole 1
directions: Cook rice with margarine.
Mix in Cheez Whiz while rice is hot. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fish soup(fiskesuppe)
directions: Cook vegetables in saucepan about 10 minutes or until tender with water to cover.
Reserve.
At same time, put fish in another saucepan with water to cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes.
Remove and keep hot.
Reserve liquid.
Combine all liquids, including cooked vegetables and butter.
Mix flour with some of milk and add to liquids.
Add remaining spices and cook over low heat, simmering 10 to 15 minutes.
Add fish, parsley and chives before serving.

title: red river chicken gumbo
directions: Boil and bone chicken.

To the broth, add bouillon cubes, tomato paste, Ro-Tel, stewed tomatoes, ketchup and white onion. Cook until tender, then add oregano, spices, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, celery salt, Tabasco, corn, field peas, salt and pepper, then add sugar and okra.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes.
Add chicken before serving.
Serve with corn bread.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and allow meat to marinate 36 to 48 hours. Grill over charcoal until fork-tender; don't overcook.
During grilling, brush occasionally with marinade.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and the cinnamon; mix with the apples.
Place apples in deep 9-inch pie pan lined with pie crust.
Pile high in center.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Mix remaining sugar, flour and melted butter; sprinkle evenly over the apples.
Place in a brown paper bag.
Fold over ends and secure with paper clips.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion.
Drain well.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: clam spaghetti or scallop fettucini
directions: Cook garlic and onion in olive oil until soft.
Add green pepper/pimento and cook 5 minutes.
Add clams with juice, parsley, pepper, salt, thyme and juice or wine.
Simmer uncovered 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add sauce and toss well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and flour.
Add milk, butter and vanilla; blend well and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until pie firms in middle.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes; drain and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until mixed.
Drop by tablespoons into hot shortening and fry until done, turning once.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in large bowl in microwave. Stir until smooth.
Mix in sugar and cereal.
Mix with hands. Form into 1/2-inch balls.
Chill on waxed paper lined baking sheet in refrigerator until firm.
Melt chips and paraffin in small saucepan or microwave on 50% power.
With toothpick, dip balls in chocolate and put back on paper to chill in refrigerator. Paraffin allows them to be stored at room temperature without melting.
Makes about 50.

title: turkey bacon spaghetti
directions: Fry bacon, green peppers and onions in olive oil until tender. Cook the spaghetti until done and drain.
Keep from sticking together by adding Italian dressing and tossing.
Put turkey bacon mixture and spaghetti all together and toss with lots of Parmesan cheese and more Italian dressing, if needed.
I like the Louis Rich bacon the best.

title: sweet and sour beef kabobs
directions: Drain pineapple juice; reserve chunks for later use.
Combine pineapple juice, Worcestershire sauce, honey and salt.
Place beef cubes in a snug fitting bowl.
Pour sauce mixture over meat. Cover and seal.
Refrigerate about eight hours.
Arrange meat, vegetables and pineapple alternately on skewers.
Broil over hot charcoal.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm (hot) water and set aside.
Pour boiling water over Crisco, salt and sugar.
Stir until dissolved. When lukewarm, add beaten egg.
Stir, then add yeast.
Add flour gradually until soft dough forms.
Cover; put in refrigerator overnight.
Grease pan.
Roll dough out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush rolls with melted butter and let rise 2 hours or longer.
Bake in 400° oven 15 or 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 24 rolls.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut up onion and brown with hamburger; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients with hamburger in skillet.
Heat for 10 minutes.

title: easy cheesy macaroni
directions: In a 10-inch skillet (sprayed with nonstick cooking spray), heat soup, milk, mustard and pepper to boiling.
Add vegetables. Return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in tuna, macaroni and cheese.
Heat thoroughly, until cheese is melted. Serves 6.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Form into ball and roll into sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Pour contents of one can of cherry pie filling into a square baking dish.
Sprinkle contents of one package of cake mix over the cherry pie filling.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: herbal moth repellent
directions: You will need small squares of double-layer cheesecloth or muslin.

title: mints
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook to 232°.
Remove from heat.
Cool 10 minutes.
Tint with coloring and add flavoring. Beat until creamy.
Keep the saucepan over very hot water while forming patties.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: aunt julia's lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add to lemon juice,
then add to beaten egg yolks.
Pour in water.
Cook in top of double boiler until thickened.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Add meringue.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Prepare crust; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, at medium speed beat cream cheese sugar, pumpkin and spices until combined.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until well mixed.
Pour into crust.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool on wire rack to room temperature.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: open-faced grilled cheese
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place cheese on each slice of toast.
Top with tomato slice.
Place in broiler pan.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes.

title: no fat banana bread
directions: Spray loaf pan.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix together applesauce, honey, egg whites, bananas and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and stir gently to blend; fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, until knife comes out clean.
Keep frozen or refrigerated.

title: frito pie
directions: Layer chili, sour cream, Fritos and cheese in a bowl.
Enjoy.

title: snickerdoodles (a not-too-sweet cookie)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together. Sift dry ingredients together and then add to shortening mixture. Chill dough 1 hour or more. Roll into balls the size of walnuts. Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in a bowl and roll dough balls in this. Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Watch carefully as the sugar coating can make them burn easily.

title: tofu patties
directions: Wrap the tofu in a clean cloth and squeeze out the water. Place the tofu and other ingredients in a bowl.
Add salt and pepper and mix well.
Form into patties and fry in deep fat until browned.
Drain on a paper towel and serve with any sauce.

title: sandy's breakfast burritos
directions: Fry hash browns and when about half done, add chorizo that has been removed from its casing.
Crumble the sausage into the potatoes and continue cooking.
Beat the eggs with the evaporated milk, salt and pepper; scramble over low heat.
In the meantime, warm tortillas in a warm skillet without shortening.
Heat tortillas just until soft; put on a warm plate or in a tortilla warmer and keep warm in very low oven.
Serve everything in separate dishes to let everyone take what they want.

title: sausage and asparagus skillet supper
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and remove fat.
Add asparagus pieces, potatoes and enough water to cook in.
Simmer about 20 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add cheese just before serving.

title: sara's mexican meat dip
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef with chopped onions.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Then add eggs, vanilla, oil and pecans.
Last add chopped apples.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, nuts and coconut (optional) in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, margarine, milk and peanut butter.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Take off heat and add vanilla.
Pour over dry ingredients, mixing well.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown sausage; drain off fat.
Melt cheese thoroughly in double boiler.
Mix all together and spread on rye slices.
Can be frozen at this point.
When ready to serve, bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: sakatomato sandwich
directions: Stack in order.
Broil until bacon is crisp and cheese is melted.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut up fryer into pieces.
Melt margarine in shallow pan. Beat egg and milk.
Dip chicken pieces in egg and milk mixture, then roll in mixture of flour, baking powder, paprika and salt. Place pieces, skin side down, in buttered pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn pieces and bake 30
minutes longer or until tender.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook and debone chicken. Shred meat into chunks and put back into boiler.
Add broth and enough water to cover chicken. Bring to a rolling boil.
Tear tortillas into small pieces and toss into slow boiling mixture. Cook over low-medium heat, keeping dumplings stirred, for 25 minutes or until desired thickness. Enjoy.

title: almond chicken
directions: Mix chicken with 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, sugar, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil over high heat.
Add chicken; toss fry until meat turns white.
Add white wine, mushrooms, water chestnuts, onion and peas; stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add celery; stir another minute. Add the chicken broth; simmer, covered, for 5 minutes over low heat.
Thicken pan juices with 1 tablespoon cornstarch mixed with soy sauce.
Taste; correct seasonings as desired.
Add toasted almonds just before serving.

title: peanut butter crunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. In large mixer bowl, blend sugar, peanut butter and cake mix on low speed until crumbly. Reserve 2/3 cup crumb mixture; set aside. Blend remaining crumb mixture, the eggs and water on low speed until moistened, scraping bowl constantly. Beat on medium speed 4 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Spread batter in pan. Sprinkle reserved mixture over batter. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over top. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.

title: surprise salad
directions: Mix all together and add nuts and marshmallows, if desired.

title: sand tarts(real old german style)
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Slowly add flour, working well.
Add well beaten eggs and mix thoroughly.
Chill overnight. Roll out thin on lightly floured board.
Brush cookies with egg white.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Press 1/2 pecan into center of cookie.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: royal brittle candy
directions: Spread nuts, cherries and pineapple in a pan about 1/2-inch thick.
Blend sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cook to 300° without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in food color to tint along with oil of orange.
Pour hot syrup back and forth over nut mixture to cover all.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well mixed.
Stir in flour, salt and vanilla until well mixed.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: lollipops
directions: Put the water in a pan.
Add a spoonful of sugar and continue to add sugar while over heat.
When sugar is dissolved, turn up the heat and bring the mixture to a boil.
Boil for a minute. Then stir into container.
To make lollipop, use popsicle sticks.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and soup.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat all together and add nuts and raisins. Bake in moderate oven until done.

title: dretke's taco salad
directions: Brown and drain chuck.
Stir in 1 can water and seasoning mix. Can be prepared night before.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put in a pie or quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with unsalted tortilla chips.

title: applesauce cake
directions: I use a small amount of cocoa to help darken cake; not enough to taste.

title: barbecue tuna
directions: Mix together.
Add tuna.
Bake at 400°
for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve on toast.

title: sherry's caramel cake
directions: Blend on high for 2 minutes.
