Divide between 3 greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: potato "cream cheese" casserole
directions: Combine mashed potatoes and cheese.
Beat until well blended. Add eggs, fresh onion, chives, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spoon into a well-greased casserole dish. Top with canned onion rings. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: cheesy chicken roll-ups
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in butter in medium skillet until tender.
Stir 1 cup cheese, sour cream, picante sauce and pepper into chicken.

title: ever-ready bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a very large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
This can be kept as long as 6 weeks.
When ready to bake, spoon batter into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 5 1/2 dozen.
tags: box wheat bran flakes cereal with raisins

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix sugar and flour well; add milk.
Bring to a slow boil. Add small amount of mixture to egg yolks; beat well, then pour yolks into rest of flour mixture.
Add coconut and let thicken, then add vanilla.
Remove from heat; pour into pie shells.

title: carl's blueberry pie
directions: Line baked pie shells with sliced bananas.
Cream lemon juice, sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over bananas.
Pour half pie filling over each pie.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 1 hour. May wait until ready to serve to add Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bacon cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in pecans or Grape-Nuts cereal.
Makes 3 medium balls.

title: griddle cakes(pancakes)
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 10 (6-inch) pancakes.

title: deloris stanfield's corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well and add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until tender. Drain.

title: pistachio munchies
directions: Mix together the butter and onion soup mix in a large glass measuring cups.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in the pistachios.
Place in resealable plastic bags for traveling.

title: stuffed roast duck
directions: Bring to boil in covered saucepan over full gas flame the ducks, salt, pepper, bay leaf, celery leaves, parsley, onion, carrot and water to cover; reduce flame to simmer (200° to 225° dial setting on controlled burner) and continue cooking 1 hour. Remove from flame and let stand until cold.
Drain.
Stuff ducks and place on rack in shallow pan.
Place over breast of each duck 2 slices of bacon or thin salt pork.
Roast in moderate gas oven (325°) for 20 minutes per pound.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mushroom vinaigrette dressing*
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Toss with cleaned mushrooms (can be stored in fridge for days).
Cut lettuce into 6 to 8 wedges. Spoon dressing over and serve.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; add chopped vegetables and add 1 (16 ounce) bottle Italian dressing and 1 bottle McCormick Salad Supreme. Toss gently.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: cajun dourga (eggplant sticks)
directions: Peel eggplant.
As it is sliced, place in bowl of 1 quart of water and 1 tablespoon of salt.
Drain.
Place in shallow dish containing hot sauce and turn to coat well.
Cover and let stand for 30 minutes.
In plastic bag, place 1 cup of flour and pepper. Drop eggplant in bag in small batches to coat with mixture and fry in deep fat fryer until golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Serve while hot.
Serves 10 to 12 as hors d'oeuvres.

title: maple syrup frosting
directions: Put in double boiler and beat very well.
Makes enough for double layer.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook and bone chicken and place in buttered casserole.
Mix soups and sour cream and put over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers; mix with butter and top casserole.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over cereal.
Let stand until lukewarm. Do not stir.
Combine Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over cereal and stir.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: snow cream
directions: Put on your boots and run outside to where there is fresh snow.
Lightly scrape off the very top of the snow.
With a big cooking spoon, scoop up the snow into a large pan (we always used the old green enamel "popcorn" bowl).
Run back inside quickly, because you usually didn't even wear a coat, so the snow doesn't begin to melt!
Pour a little milk and sugar into the snow and stir until about the consistency of partially melted ice cream. Add a "tad" of vanilla and enjoy!
Don't eat too fast or it will give you a headache!

title: slice nut cookies
directions: Add sugars and shortening.
Mix eggs together, then dry ingredients.
Stir, then add pecans.
Make 3 rolls; wrap into foil.
Freeze.
Slice thin.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: lollypops
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook at 300° without stirring, to hard crack stage.

title: fried fish
directions: Either fillet whole fish or cut up into smaller pieces (size of 3 fingers approximately).
Rinse and let drain.
Put oil into deep fryer.
Amount of oil needed will depend on size of fryer and amount of fish to be fried.
Heat to approximately 400°.
Sprinkle pepper and Lawry's salt on both sides of fish.
Lawry's salt should just about cover the fish, but not too thick.
Put meal (3 to 4 cups) in a doubled grocery bag.
Put several pieces of fish in bag and shake until coated with meal.
Deep fry until golden brown. Slice potatoes; sprinkle with Lawry's salt.
Coat with meal and then fry.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni for 6 to 7 minutes; drain.
Put in 9 to 12-inch baking dish.
Add melted margarine and cheese.
Beat eggs in milk. Add to macaroni.
Spread a little cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: onion pie
directions: Partially bake a 9-inch pie crust.
Saute onions in oil and butter over low heat until golden yellow.
Beat together the eggs, half and half, flour, salt and pepper, then add onions and half the grated cheese.
Pour into crust; sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: baklava
directions: To make the stuffing, combine and mix walnuts, sugar and cardamom.
Set aside.

title: deep-dish pudding
directions: Place 1/2 of cake in glass bowl (punch bowl). Pour 1/2 of the pudding over cake. Add remaining cake. Top with remaining pudding. Top with Cool Whip.

title: scallops in garlic butter
directions: Thaw
scallops	if frozen.
Cut large scallops in half. Cook and stir the scallops
and	garlic in margarine or butter for 3 to 5 minutes or
until
scallops
turn
opaque.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate pie deluxe
directions: Heat marshmallows, milk and chocolate until blended.
Chill until thickened.
Beat whipping cream until thick.
Fold marshmallow mixture into whipped cream.
Pour into crust and chill 3 hours or until set.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Cook, drain and set aside elbow macaroni.
Brown ground beef. Drain; return to large Dutch oven.
Add onion, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Saute until onion is tender.
Add chopped tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes. Add macaroni; salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 5 minutes and serve.

title: yummy meat balls
directions: Mix ground chuck, onion soup and eggs together into small balls.
Combine other ingredients.
Simmer and pour over meat balls in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: canned green beans
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to a boil.
After they start boiling, cook 15 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: 4-in-one cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugars and eggs in mixing bowl; beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to shortening mixture.
Mix.
Stir in vanilla and oats.
Add pecans and chocolate chips.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: el chorro chicken and cheese enchiladas(chicken enchiladas)
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water or chicken stock until done. Drain liquid, reserving 1/4 cup.
Shred chicken and mix with cream cheese, heavy cream and red onion.

title: creamy potato bake(cooking time:  50 minutes)
directions: Preparation:
Over low heat, gradually blend milk into cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in chives, onion and 1 teaspoon salt. Add potatoes and stir gently.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and chill.
Before serving, bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Stir and bake, uncovered, 20 minutes longer.
Stir again.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Stir potatoes, sour cream, soup (undiluted) and cheeses together.
Bake in oven at 350° until bubbly.
Crush corn flakes and add to melted butter.
Top potatoes with this mixture and continue to cook 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lea ann's pie
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Add pecans, coconut and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand 20 minutes, then add margarine, brown and white sugars.
Mix well.
Then add eggs, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken, then dip into butter.
Dredge into the following ingredients:
Parmesan cheese, corn flake crumbs and Hidden Valley dressing mix.
Bake uncovered in well-greased baking dish in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Use some of the melted margarine to grease an 8-inch square pan.
Mix the rest of the margarine with all of the ingredients. Pour into the greased pan.
Dot with 3 to 4 pats margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Great as a side dish or starch served with poultry.

title: spinach rice pie
directions: Cook rice; cook spinach according to package directions and drain well.
Beat 2 eggs and cream cheese together.
Salt to taste.
Combine this mixture with spinach, rice, onions and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Grease 2 pie tins and divide mixture into them.
Beat remaining egg and pour half over each pie.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese over pies.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: oreo freak out
directions: Layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan in the order listed. Sprinkle reserved cookie crumbs on top of Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Let stand at room temperature a few minutes prior to serving.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt oleo and combine with crushed cracker crumbs; reserve 1/4 cup.
Mix all ingredients; place in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle reserved 1/4 cup crumbs on top.

title: crab and shrimp bake for two
directions: Mix together crab, shrimp, cream cheese, milk and onion. Cover with almonds.
Bake in a buttered casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash.
Drain off water.
Add crackers, margarine, 2 eggs, onion, soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple-cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and let stand for 2 hours.
Mix together 2 small packages of lemon Jell-O and 2 cups hot water (because of the juice in pineapple, I reduce the water to 1 3/4 cups).
Add to first mixture, pour into molds and refrigerate.

title: apricot brandy pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients in order.
Alternate flour and sour cream. Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
Bake in tube pans.

title: macaroni dessert
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Rinse with cold water many times and drain well while cold.
Drain and save juice from fruit.
To the juice, add sugar, eggs, flour and salt. Mix well and cook over medium heat until thickened (will be a thin syrup).
Pour syrup over cooled pasta.
Refrigerate several hours, preferably overnight.
Juice mixture will be absorbed.

title: spice ball
directions: With a pencil or crayon, mark styrofoam ball into 8 equal sections.
Along these lines, insert whole cloves to outline the sections.
Cover one section at a time with white glue, then sprinkle with one of the spices until styrofoam is completely covered.
Alternate sections of whole and ground spices.
Let the ball dry, then decorate with a sprig of holly or pine.
Make a loop of the ribbon and pin it to the ball so it can be hung.

title: chicken athena
directions: In a skillet brown chicken in oil, add onion and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and marinade from artichokes.
Cook over medium heat 10 - 15 minutes or until thickened a bit, stirring frequently.
Stir in artichoke hearts.
Heat through. Top with Feta cheese.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 layers of waxed paper and pound with wooden mallet until as thin as possible.
Chop fresh bread slices in blender until chopped fine.
Pour milk on plate and sprinkle with black pepper.
Dip chicken in milk and pepper and then in fresh bread crumbs.
Fry in margarine in skillet over medium heat.
When chicken begins to brown, squeeze lemon juice over chicken.
Use 1/2 lemon on each chicken breast.
Be generous with lemon juice.
Arrange chicken on platter and decorate with lemon slices.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender with peeling on.
Cool, peel and dice into small pieces.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Do not use salad dressing, mayonnaise only.
This will make a large bowl of salad.

title: delicious banana muffins
directions: Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These are great!

title: heavenly pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Beat 1 minute.
Add cake flour, baking powder, vanilla and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Spread batter in a greased, floured pan 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and beat, then water and flour.
Cook on long sheet pan.
Turn out on cloth sprinkled with a little sugar.
Spread with jelly and roll up.
Bake at 350° to 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: cherry loin roast
directions: Place roast fat side up on rack in shallow pan.
Insert meat thermometer in center of roast.
Roast uncovered in preheated 325 degree oven allowing 30 - 35 minutes per pound.
Thermometer should register 170 degrees.

title: chocolate walnut whispers
directions: Melt chocolate chips in pan over hot (not boiling) water.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Beat in vanilla and vinegar.
Fold in melted chocolate and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and place on wire racks to cool.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: ravioli in tarragon cream
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine over medium heat. Stir in Prosciutto and saute 1 minute. Add cream and tarragon; season with salt and pepper. Simmer 2 minutes or until cream is slightly thickened.

title: brown beauty icing
directions: Set bowl in ice water.
Mix sugar, salt, milk, shortening, chocolate and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Add eggs; beat until thick and of spreading consistency, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut stalk off broccoli and cut head into pieces.
Boil the broccoli and strain.
Melt desired Velveeta cheese in microwave, then spread cheese over broccoli in a casserole dish.
Saute mushrooms in a skillet with 1 teaspoon of butter and add to mixture in dish.
Then crumble Ritz crackers and spread over top of mixture.
Serves 6.

title: sugar-free strawberry spread
directions: Soften gelatin in grape juice in cup.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil and simmer, uncovered, for 9 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin mixture to dissolve.
After cooling, store in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: chocolate covered cherry pie
directions: In microwave, melt together.
Add 1 can cherry pie filling. Stir and put into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Before serving, top with sweetened whipped cream.
Garnish with chopped walnuts and sliced maraschino cherries sprinkled over whipped cream.
An easy, attractive, great and different pie.

title: banana pudding
directions: Chill the Eagle Brand milk in refrigerator.
Mix pudding and whole milk. Beat and put in refrigerator until good and thick, then add the Eagle Brand.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a large bowl, layer wafers, bananas and pudding; repeat.
Chill.

title: devil's food pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Combine ingredients; pour into pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 25 minutes.
Invert; cool completely.
Microwave 1/4 cup frosting; drizzle over cake.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except mints.
Put mint in middle of 1 tablespoon of dough.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer chicken, onion and Doritos.
Pour warmed mixture of tomatoes and soup over the layers.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Add cheese; bake 10 more minutes.

title: chicken scampi(easy, fast and good!)
directions: In a skillet, heat together butter and olive oil; saute green onions and garlic.
Add lemon juice, chicken, salt, pepper and parsley.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, for 5 to 8 minutes or until chicken is done.
Add tomatoes and heat through. Serve over buttered noodles or hot rice.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Sift all dry ingredients, adding nuts and raisins.
Mix all together, leaving persimmons until last, mixing well.
Bake in oven at 300° for 2 hours and 10 minutes.

title: sweet-sour salad dressing
directions: Put in jar and shake well.

title: mary's oatmeal, pecan and gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars. Beat eggs and vanilla and add to creamed mixture. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Add to first mixture. Stir in oatmeal, chopped nuts and chopped candy. Bake at 375° until brown (10 to 15 minutes). Make the size of cookie you desire.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Grate other cheeses.
Mix well all ingredients.
Form one large ball or 3 small ones.
Cover foil with paprika.
Roll balls on foil until well covered.
Set in refrigerator overnight or several hours.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: cherry crunch delight
directions: In an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer ingredients as listed. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Yields 15 servings.

title: asparagus chicken
directions: Stir together cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce, water and garlic. Add chicken and marinate for at least 1 hour.
In wok or heavy skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken and marinate, then the asparagus. Stir-fry 3 minutes or until chicken is cooked and asparagus is tender.

title: low-fat watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: lemon mayonnaise
directions: Combine mayonnaise and lemonade concentrate.
Blend well. Fold in whipped cream.
Serve this over fruit.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pickled string beans(7 pints)
directions: Wash and cut end of beans;
leave whole.
Pack beans in jars. Add all ingredients before or after you pack jars.

title: easy chicken
directions: Stir sauce ingredients together in baking dish.
Place chicken in sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in large baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: barbecue spice rub
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Rub on ribs, beef brisket, pork shoulder, etc.
Grill over hot coals.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Brown chicken strips, one half at a time.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in refrigerator.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples with sugar and let stand.
Combine flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to apple mixture.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream small curd cottage cheese and cream cheese in bowl.
Add sugar gradually, beating.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in lemon juice, vanilla, cornstarch and flour.
Add melted butter; mix until smooth.
Blend in sour cream.
Pour into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let cake remain for 2 hours.
Cool 1 hour out of oven before refrigerating.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Make Jell-O with hot water, sugar and the juice of 2 lemons. Chill Jell-O until starts to set.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat vanilla and cream cheese. Add sour cream and sugar; beat until mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put into graham cracker crust. Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with cherries or your favorite topping.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice eggplant into about 1/4-inch thick slices.
Heat enough olive oil to cover bottom of large skillet.
Dip slices of eggplant alternately in egg, then bread crumbs.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Lay on paper towel to absorb excess oil.
You will need to add extra oil to continue frying.
In a small saucepan, saute the onion in water, then add the tomato puree.
Cook about 25 minutes.

title: corn and okra combo
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water. Set aside. Saute onion and green peppers in butter until crisp and tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: stove top candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sugars and water in large skillet; let boil 5 minutes to make syrup.
Add margarine, salt and vanilla.
Stir.
Add potatoes; sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Put lid on skillet; turn to medium heat and cook for 20 minutes or until tender. While the potatoes are cooking, spoon some of the syrup over them so they won't dry out.

title: hot tuna sandwich
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spread on bread and top with slice of cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: green rice
directions: Boil broccoli in salt water about 15 minutes; drain.
Heat Cheez Whiz and chicken soup and mix with broccoli.
Melt oleo and saute onions, then add to broccoli mix.
Add cooked rice and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Reserve some beef to roll cheese ball in.

title: steak casserole
directions: Fry steaks lightly and arrange in casserole dish.
Place onion on top of steak.
Next put mushrooms and juice.
Mix tomato rice soup and 1 can water with little hot sauce and 1/2 cup catsup. Pour over steak.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix
yellow
cake
mix,
except add 1 tablespoon peanut butter with
the first 1/2 cup water and last fold in chopped peanuts. Bake according to cake mix directions.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill until ready to serve.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: spinach and mushroom quiche
directions: Beat eggs just enough to combine the yolks and whites. Add the cheese which has been grated.
Add cream or milk, salt, pepper and basil.
Put the spinach and mushrooms in the crust.
Pour the egg mixture over it. Add a little milk to fill the pan about 1/4-inch from top. Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Remove from oven. Arrange a sliced tomato on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until the quiche is firm.

title: sliced beef cheese balls
directions: Cut beef and onions together; add cream cheese.
Mix all together and save one package of beef to put on top of ball. Serve with crackers.

title: steve's crawfish etouffee
directions: In iron skillet, make
a medium to dark roux with flour and oil.
Add onions, bell peppers, garlic and parsley to halt roux's browning.
Let
simmer
for
10 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Beat together all ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pour in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, testing with a toothpick to make sure it's done.

title: diane's coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients to form batter.
Pour 1/2 of the batter in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix the last 2 ingredients together. Sprinkle mixture over the batter in pan. Pour second layer of batter over the sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: baptist baked spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef in large skillet; drain. Add kidney beans, tomato sauce and tomato soup (prepare soup according to directions on can).
Add Ragu sauce.
Add onions and chili powder to taste.
Stir and let simmer.
In separate pan prepare spaghetti in large casserole dish.
Add beef and tomato sauce from skillet.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Suggestion:
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: lemon delight dessert
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Bring the cocoa, oleo and water to melt and boil.
Remove from heat.
Sift together the sugar and flour.
Pour cocoa mixture on flour mixture.
Add the eggs, buttermilk, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes (in an oblong pan).

title: eggs and sausage casserole(prepare same day.  serves 6.)
directions: Spray a 7 x 11-inch casserole with Pam.
Cover bottom of dish with 1/2 of the cheese.
Mix salt, paprika and mustard into the sour cream and pour 1/2 of this over cheese.
Sprinkle with sausage and top with remaining sour cream.
Pour eggs on top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes until firm.

title: microwave blueberry syrup
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a 1-quart casserole.
Add water and lemon juice.
Stir in blueberries.
Cook on High (full power) for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes.
Great on waffles or pancakes.

title: lisa's stuffed cornbread
directions: Brown meat, onions and green peppers; add in optional items, drain.
Mix cornbread as directed on the box.
Spray a baking dish, 9 x 13 inches.
Put down half the cornbread mix to covering the bottom of the dish.
Then, put all of the meat mixture on top of this.
Add grated cheese.
Place second
half of the corn bread mixture on top.
Bake at 350 degrees until brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease a tube pan with butter.
Beat butter until light. Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time while beating and alternate with portions of flour until all is used.
Add flavoring.
Bake about 1 hour at 300°.

title: mediterranean fish stew
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil in 3-quart saucepan until tender.
Stir in salt, thyme, basil, saffron, bay leaf and red pepper.
Stir in clam juice, chicken broth and tomatoes; heat to boiling.
Simmer 5 minutes to blend flavors.
Stir in zucchini. Simmer until zucchini is almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and fish.
Simmer just until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork and shrimp are hot through.
Serve hot stew with lemon slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy apple dessert
directions: Spread apple pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spread cake mix on top, then pecans on top of cake mix.
Slice margarine on top of nuts; sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
This keeps well, even in refrigerator, without getting soggy for 3 to 4 days.
Can be made with any fruit pie filling.

title: grilled deer meat
directions: Marinate meat
at
least 4 hours or overnight.	Cook on grill until done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cut in shortening with 2 knives or a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and water; stir until mixture forms a ball.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured board.
Fit into a 9-inch pie pan; crimp edges to seal.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork.
Bake at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: roquefort cream dressing(aunt mary's recipe)
directions: Cut out root ends and chop finely, tops and all, to make scallions.
Combine mayonnaise, garlic and chopped parsley.
Add to mixture the anchovy paste.
Combine and add sour cream and vinegar. Add lemon juice to thin mixture.
Add Roquefort or Blue cheese, crumbled.
Season with pepper (no salt; anchovy paste is salty). Chill.
Will keep for 1 month.
Use as salad dressing or on crackers or tomato aspic.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into 1/4-inch strips.
Coat with salt and pepper; brown with onion.
Add garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon and catsup.
Pour over meat and cook for 40 minutes over low heat. Add wine, mushrooms and dissolved flour and stir until blended. Cook 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir in sour cream. Remove from heat and serve over rice or noodles.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together nutmeg, cinnamon, oil and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place softened butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl and mix well.
Add baking soda, flour and baking powder and mix well.
Add oats, rice, cereal, coconut, candies and nuts (or stir-in of your choice) and stir with a spoon until well blended. Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
If desired, add toppings (candy corn, etc.) as cookies cool.

title: baked eggs with cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice eggs and arrange alternate layers of crumbs, egg and cheese in a well-greased casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour cream over mixture; sprinkle with crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french cherry dessert
directions: Mix crackers, butter and sugar together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package.
Mix the powdered sugar and cream cheese. Blend the two mixtures together; spread on crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; drain.
Combine with soup and put into casserole dish.
Cover with cheese slices.
Cube bread and sprinkle over cheese.
Drizzle melted butter over bread and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a 10-inch greased tube pan.
Cover pan with foil and place a pan of water on bottom rack under cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain; mix all ingredients together.
Drain olives.
Best if made the day before and refrigerated.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine with water in top of double boiler over hot water.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Blend small amount of butter mixture into beaten yolks, then add to remaining butter. Beat mixture with rotary beater until thickened and smooth, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Blend in lemon juice.
Serve immediately. Yield: 1 cup.

title: oven beef burgundy
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in large skillet; do not pour off drippings.
Remove bacon; crumble and set aside.
Add beef, about half at a time, to drippings in skillet.
Brown over medium-high heat.
Transfer to 3-quart casserole.

title: frijoles con dulce(sweet beans)
directions: Clean and boil beans until tender (2 hours).
Pass them through a food processor and sift them twice using some milk if necessary.
Add the remaining milk, coconut milk and mix well. Add sugar, salt and spices.
Cook over medium heat; add sweet potatoes and raisins.
Cook 20 minutes longer.
Add butter.
Serve in small bowls with casabe (cassava bread from Indians) or toast, or unsalted crackers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine the pumpkin, sugar and spices.
Blend in eggs, milk and evaporated milk.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and outside of pie comes out clean.
Cool.

title: zesty italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in roasting pan and brush with oleo.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon salad dressing mix.
Bake 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and broth.
Sprinkle with remaining salad dressing mix.
Bake 25 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: pineapple layer cake
directions: Sift flour together with baking powder and salt in small bowl. Cream butter and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs and mix. Combine evaporated milk with pineapple juice.
Alternately add flour mixture and liquid, mixing after each addition.
Add vanilla with mixture.
Beat with hand mixer about 1 minute.
Pour into two greased and floured layer pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Let cake cool, then prepare layers by spreading Pineapple Filling between each layer, ending with filling on top.
Chill before serving.

title: multi-fruit trifle
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and gelatin, stir in water until smooth. Bring to a boil, cook and stir for 2-3 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat and stir in strawberries, set aside. In a mixing bowl, combine milk and pudding mix, beat on low for 2 minutes, set aside. Toss bananas with lemon juice, drain and set aside. Place half of the cake cubes in a trifle bowl or 3-quart serving bowl. Layer with half of the pudding, bananas, strawberry sauce, pineapple and whipped cream. Repeat layers. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Garnish with additional fruit if desired.

title: caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 C milk in saucepan. Mix in bowl melted margarine, 1/3 C milk and cake mix. Put 1/2 of cake mixture in greased pan. Cook at 350 degrees for 6 minutes.

title: cabbage scallop
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces and cook rapidly in boiling water 7 to 8 minutes until barely tender, but still crisp.
Drain well.
Make white sauce.
In a greased baking dish layer cabbage, bacon, pimentos, cheese and a sprinkling of bread crumbs.
Cover with sauce and remaining crumbs.
Bake 375 to 10 - 15 minutes until bubbly.

title: cribbage
directions: In a large pot, brown hamburger meat with onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add V-8.
Put in cabbage and celery.
Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until it falls off the bone. Remove all bones and tear chicken into small pieces. Place chicken in bottom of baking dish. Mix soups and milk in blender, if you have one. Use a cup of broth that the chicken was cooked in and mix with the stuffing mix. Sprinkle over top of soup mixture and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: crab louis
directions: Shred lettuce on plates.
Place shredded crabmeat on top of lettuce.
Cut tomatoes and eggs in wedges.
Circle atop salads. Pour 1/4 cup Louise dressing over each salad; dash with paprika.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all, but only enough oil to make dough soft enough to put into presser.
Bake at 350° until done, about 10 to 12 minutes. Do not brown.

title: two 'n' one casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with cheese last 20 minutes of cooking time.
If using other meat, use 1/2 cup milk instead of broth.
Can use 1/2 cup noodles and 1/2 cup spaghetti.

title: walnut balls
directions: Cream butter and vanilla.
Blend in sugar, flour and nuts. Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Makes 24 balls.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Drain oysters, rinse, pat dry with paper towels and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Cut bacon slices in half crosswise.
You will need 1/2 bacon slice per oyster.

Wrap each oyster with 1/2 bacon slice and skewer with toothpick to secure bacon (dampen each toothpick before inserting through oysters and bacon to prevent the toothpicks from charring while cooking).
Place oysters on broiler pan and broil each side until bacon is cooked.

title: hopscotch - so easy, so good
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips (Medium in microwave).
Stir until blended.
Add noodles and marshmallows until coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper on cookie sheets. Chill until firm.
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen, depending on size.

title: light brown brownies
directions: Mix together and
put into an 8 x 8-inch pan (well-greased). Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Let brownies cool for 15 minutes. Cut into squares and remove from pan.

title: ruth's tea cakes
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Drain beans; put in large bowl and mix with electric mixer. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 regular or 2 deep-dish pies.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8-inch pie shell. Bake at 375°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs, soda, flour, sour cream and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients
together and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: cindy's spaghetti salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, mustard, sugar and vinegar (makes almost 3 cups.
Combine with other ingredients.

title: apple pie
directions: Put the water in the pot.
Put the hot dogs in the pot.
Cook them for one minute.

title: hush puppies
directions: *Omit soda, baking powder and salt.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar together, then add remaining ingredients.
Beat together until smooth and fold in 5 egg whites (beaten stiffly).
Grease and flour 3 round cake pans.
Pour batter into pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: super dogs
directions: If using self-rising flour, omit salt and baking powder.
Mix together all but wieners.
Dry wieners with paper towel and roll in mixture.
Fry in hot grease.
Drain and serve with ketchup and mustard.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Pat out on round pizza pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread on crust.
Arrange circles of fruit with cherry in middle, then pineapple, mandarin orange slices, strawberry slices, banana slices and pecan halves alternately until pizza crust is fully covered.
Slice as any pizza.

title: heavenly hash browns
directions: Separate the thawed potatoes.
Mix together the onion, soup and sour cream and toss with potatoes.
Fold in cheese, chives, pepper and salt.
Mix crumbs and melted butter and spread over mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 to 60 minutes at 350° or until done.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, sugar and baking powder; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine butter, eggs, milk, vanilla and flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in blueberries with wooden spoon.
Fill paper-lined muffin pans.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
If using frozen blueberries, do not thaw.

title: apple tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut each apple into 8 pieces and place in pie crust.
Cook in oven for 20 minutes.

title: kara's favorite raspberry ring
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add juice drained from raspberries, ice cream and lemonade.
Stir until well mixed.
Let stand until slightly jelled.
Add raspberries and nuts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix and let jell good.
Can be served on lettuce, if like to, with a 1/2 teaspoon mayonnaise on top or serve plain.

title: pudding cake
directions: Soften oleo, blend with flour and pecan pieces.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool crust. Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Beat together puddings and milk.
Spread this over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and pecans. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: tomato sauce with prosciutto and portobello mushrooms
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Over low to medium heat, saute onions and garlic until transparent.
Add oregano, basil and mushrooms and stir until mushrooms change color and darken, about 3 to 5 minutes. Add whole and crushed tomatoes, breaking up the whole tomatoes to make a chunky texture.
(You may need to add water to thin the sauce slightly so that it will cook.)
Add red wine and bring to a low boil.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
During the last 15 minutes, add the Prosciutto.
Don't let the Prosciutto get dry. Serve with pasta.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick cheeseburger pie(one dish dinner)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cook beef and onion in skillet until brown.
Drain.
Stir in soup, veggies and milk.
Stir baking mix and water together until moist. Spread evenly in bottom of baking dish.
Spread beef mixture over batter; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: steak diane
directions: Brown thin slices very quickly in butter, about 1 minute each side, turning once.
Remove to warm serving dish.
To drippings in pan, add remaining ingredients.
Swirl over heat to blend.
Serve at once.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: sandwich on a bun
directions: You put your buns on a plate.
You put ketchup, mustard and mayonnaise on there.
Then you put your meat.
Put the buns together.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter toast and slither 12 slices of bread (edges trimmed). Crumble in bottom of casserole dish (approximately 10 x 12-inches).
Cook mild sausage and hot sausage; drain and crumble. Pour on top of sausage.
Mix in bowl eggs, half and half, 1 pound sharp Cheddar cheese and salt and pepper.
Beat all together and pour on top of sausage.
Top with 1 pound mild Cheddar cheese, shredded.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant; cool and peel.
Chop in cubes.
Add eggs and stale bread, salt and pepper.
Put ham, bacon or shrimp, onion, garlic, hot pepper and bell pepper in frying pan with a small amount of grease.
Fry until brown, then add eggplant, eggs and bread to the mixture and cook until done.
Put in buttered casserole dish and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: mamie eisenhower's million dollar fudge
directions: Place chocolates, Marshmallow Whip and walnuts in a 4-quart bowl.
In a 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, butter and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until it comes to a rolling boil (cannot be stirred down).
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over chocolate mixture and stir until chocolates are melted.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 10 x 9-inch pan, lined with waxed paper.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: banana cornmeal nut bread
directions: This is a delicious alternate to banana bread!

title: scalloped oysters
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish start with a thin layer of oyster crackers, slightly crumbled, then a layer of oysters, then dot with pieces of butter or margarine.
Repeat layers to fill dish, ending with top layer being the crackers.
Fill the dish with milk and let set for a little while before baking.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: spanish paella
directions: Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with mixture.
In a 4-quart Dutch oven, brown chicken, a few pieces at a time, in hot olive oil, for 20 minutes.
Drain excess fat. Return chicken to pan.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with restaurant style tortilla chips or crackers or corn bread.
Cheese on top, if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and meat; mix into cream cheese and roll into ball.

title: venison pepper steak
directions: Brown in 2 sticks of butter the green and red peppers, onion, small pieces of deer meat and salt and pepper.
Then take ingredients out in the leftover juices.
Take a jar; mix milk and flour and make a thick gravy.
Place meat, peppers and onions back in the gravy.
Let simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Place over rice. Then eat, eat, eat!

title: lemonade cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not underbake!
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Thoroughly prick warm cake completely through to bottom with toothpick.
Gradually spoon lemony glaze over cake until completely absorbed.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Definitely a brisk-weather confection.
Coarsely grate chocolate.
Melt it with butter and add cream.
Gradually stir in confectioners sugar and hazelnuts until lump free.
Cover and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Make into individual balls by rolling about a teaspoonful of the mixture in the palm of your hand.
The warmth will cause the chocolate to melt slightly, so the final coating will adhere.
Roll balls in the coating of your choice, which will stick to them very satisfactorily.
Keep refrigerated, but for best flavor, remove 2 hours before serving.
Makes about 1/3 pound.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Stir together water, soup, carrot, onion, seasoning and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in tortellini and broccoli; cover and simmer 20 minutes more or until tortellini is tender.
Stir in chicken and Parmesan cheese.
Heat through.
Makes 4 main dishes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% Bran; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add beaten eggs to creamed shortening and sugar.
Add soaked 100% Bran.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk, alternating stirring in All-Bran.
Put in covered container in refrigerator.
Can be kept and used for 2 or 3 weeks.

title: betsy ross cake
directions: Grease and flour 4 (8 x 8-inch) pans.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in, one at a time the eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add milk alternately with the flour mixture.
Spread in pans.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti dinner
directions: Brown
hamburger,
bell
pepper and onion; drain.
Stir into spaghetti
and
ketchup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Put cheese on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Heat soups together.
Gradually add milk and stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat about 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: elaine's peach pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in boiling water.
Cook until clear.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Cool slightly. Put peaches into gelatin mixture and spoon into baked pie shell. Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Lightly oil one 15 x 11-inch baking pan.
Mix sugar, syrup and water in heavy pan.
Bring to a boil, tapping bottom of pan to help melt sugar.
Using candy thermometer, without stirring, continue boiling until hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat and add quickly oil and food coloring.
Pour in pan.
When cool, use mallet or rolling pin.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: buttered peas
directions: Put peas, onions, lettuce, sugar, salt, nutmeg, parsley and oil in a heavy saucepan.
Add boiling water.
Cover tightly and cook on high heat for 10 minutes.
Turn the heat to low and cook 10 minutes more, or until peas are tender.
Serve with some of the broth over them.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to
Add
ground beef, egg, milk and seasonings to bread
crumbs.
Mix
thoroughly
by hand.
Shape meat into a 9 x
4-inch loaf and place in shallow glass baking pan with lid.
Bake for
hour.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until very crisp and finely dice.
Pour off bacon fat from skillet, except 2 tablespoons.
Blend flour and salt into raw fat, cooking over low heat and stirring.
Gradually add water and blend.
Stir in beaten egg and vinegar.
Continue cooking and stirring over low heat until mixture thickens. Pour over dandelion greens.

title: red devil balls
directions: Mix ham and cheese until well blended.
Roll into large ball. Refrigerate until well chilled.
Roll ball in pecans.
Spread on crackers.

title: ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill until serving time. Serves 4.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple and juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Toss sliced apples with lemon juice, lemon rind and water. Mix in sugar, tapioca, spices and raisins. Place apple mixture in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch pan.

title: cheese and ham strudel
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a baking sheet.
Mix ham, Swiss and blue cheeses, celery and pepper together.
Prepare pastry by unfolding on a 20 inch long sheet of waxed paper.
Using a rolling pin, roll pastry into a 15 X 9 inch rectangle.
Spread filling lengthwise in a 5 inch strip down center of pastry within 2 inches of edges.
Fold pastry over filling to enclose, folding in short sides first.
Place strudel, seam side down, on baking sheet. Remove waxed paper.
Brush strudel with melted butter.
Bake until lightly golden, about 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°. Bake until golden brown, 30 minutes more.
Transfer baking sheet to a wire rack to cool slightly.

title: fettuccine with garlic and kale
directions: Bring large pot of salted water to boil.
Add 1 tablespoon oil. Add kale and stir until beginning to wilt, about 1 minute.
Add fettuccine and cook until just tender, but still firm to bite.

title: rhubarb-cherry crisp
directions: Bring 1 cup sugar and 1 cup water to boil.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add cherry pie filling.
Put 1/2 of crumb mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread rhubarb on top.
Spread cherry mixture on top.
Place remaining mixture on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix together 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Put cinnamon mixture in a brown bag or container with tight fitting lid. Drop 4 to 6 pieces of dough into the bag or container.
Shake until each piece is coated with sugar-cinnamon mixture. Remove from bag; drop into a buttered tube pan. Repeat process until all pieces of dough have been used.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine. Add remaining 3/4 cup sugar, remaining 1 teaspoon cinnamon and vanilla. Bring to a boil.
Pour syrup over biscuit pieces in prepared pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; immediately invert baking dish on serving platter.

title: fudgy rocky road bars
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter and chocolate.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Top with filling.

title: potato roses
directions: Peel potatoes, cut in halves and cook in boiling, lightly salted water until tender.
Mash slightly.
Place potatoes in large mixer bowl, beat until light and fluffy.
Add 1/4 cup butter, onion, salt, pepper, parsley, cheese and egg.
Whip until well mixed.
Cool.

title: pete's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and pour in gallon jar.
Finish filling with vinegar. Stir.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes.
When they come to a boil, put them in strainer and rinse.
Put potatoes back in pan.
Add all ingredients and put on low heat; cook for approximately 45 minutes to an hour.
Stir constantly so the soup won't burn.
Eat with crackers if desired. Serves 4.

title: tasty chili cheese bars(appetizer)
directions: Grate and mix cheeses together.
Line bottom of 9-inch square ovenproof dish with 1/2 of the cheese mixture.
Spread green chilies and juice over cheese mixture.
Layer remaining cheese. Pour eggs over cheese-chili mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake until set at 350°.

title: glazed lemon nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter or margarine and the 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and lemon peel.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Combine lemon juice and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Spoon over top.
Remove from pan; wrap.
Store overnight.
Enjoy!

title: mincemeat fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Stir together flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend in flour mixture.
Turn batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 45 to 50 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skins till tender.
Peel and slice while hot. Heat bacon in a skillet and add the onion and celery.
Saute till golden.
Heat the stock and remaining ingredients to boiling. Add all ingredients together and gently stir the potatoes.
Serve immediately with chopped fresh parsley.
Leftovers can be served chilled.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Brown beef in microwave at 100% for 5 minutes.
Drain off excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients and microwave at 100% for another 3 to 5 minutes.
May brown beef in skillet and add remaining ingredients.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add other ingredients and simmer for about 1 hour.
More or less chili powder and hot sauce can be added, according to how hot you like it.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Add enough cream to melt sugar.
Cook first four ingredients until it makes a soft ball or 238°.
Quickly add vanilla and butter, the size of a walnut.
Beat until creamy.
Add walnuts to coat.
Pour on waxed paper and separate quickly with a fork.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Put last three ingredients in plastic bag and shake.
Peel potatoes and cut in wedges.
Add potatoes in bag and shake.
Melt margarine in casserole.
Lay potatoes in casserole (1 layer). Sprinkle rest of flour mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
After 1/2 hour of baking, turn potatoes over.

title: ground beef-cabbage casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion in margarine.
Drain.
Mix cabbage with meat mixture and saute for 5 additional minutes, stirring often.
Place mixture in casserole dish.
Mix tomato sup and milk to pouring consistency.
Add hot pepper sauce and pour over meat and cabbage.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti about 10 minutes and drain.
Brown ground beef and garlic; drain.
Add cottage cheese, Mozzarella, salt and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Stuff each manicotti with 1/4 cup of meat-cheese mixture.
Place in a single layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle any remaining filling over manicotti.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle evenly
with oregano and generously with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 10 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Add flour gradually, 1 cup at a time. Bake at 350°.

title: hearty breakfast casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Peel and dice. Fry bacon; remove and drain, reserving bacon drippings.
Lightly brown potatoes and onion in bacon drippings.
Remove and combine with bacon, cheese, eggs and salt.
Turn into shallow buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set in center.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mock shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the ground beef with chopped onion.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Precook carrots.
Precook peas.
Remove beef from pan and remove as much grease as possible.
Put beef in large bowl.
Make gravy in frypan.
Pour over beef.
Add vegetables and mix.
Pour into ungreased cake pan (preferably Corning).
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Add cheese over top potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts and browns slightly.

title: spinach squares
directions: Cover bottom
and
inch
of
sides
of greased 9 x 13-inch pan
with
rolls.
Flatten
out the crescent rolls and press against bottom of pan to form flat crust for quiche; set aside.
In a large bowl, toss together cheeses and flour.
Mix in milk,
eggs,
salt,
pepper
and
nutmeg;
stir in spinach. Pour into
prepared crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes. Cut
into
small squares (approximately 40).
May be served immediately
as
hot
hors
d'oeuvres or made ahead and reheated on
hot
tray.
May be frozen after baking; reheat in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: caramel candy
directions: Melt sugar and butter over low heat until caramelized to a golden brown.
Add salt and milk; stir constantly until a hard ball can be formed in water.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until cool.
Pour into pan and let stand in refrigerator at least 30 minutes before cutting.
Yields about 20 (1-inch) squares.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion; drain well.
Add chicken soup, milk, taco sauce and enchilada sauce.
Layer with flour tortillas and grated cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in zucchini and set aside.
Sift flour, salt (optional), soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Mix together with egg mixture; add nuts and/or raisins.
Pour into two 8 x 4-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Leave in pans 30 minutes to cool. Remove from pans and finish cooling on racks.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine ingredients into bowl and enjoy.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Blend salt, sugar, mustard and flour; stir into onion.
Add vinegar and water slowly, stirring constantly, and cook until thick.
Blend pickle relish, celery, green pepper and diced potatoes.
Pour on the hot dressing, mixing lightly.
Serve hot.
The flavor is improved by putting the prepared salad into baking dish, covering and heating 20 minutes in a moderate oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain lima beans.
Partially cook broccoli and drain. Butter a baking dish.
First layer lima beans, second broccoli. Next, mix pepper in soup and cover vegetables.
Do not dilute soup.
Cover vegetables and soup with bread crumbs and cheese. Bake until soup is bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: honey-lemon chicken
directions: Arrange pieces of chicken in shallow baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine catsup and honey.
Pour over chicken pieces to coat on all sides.
Place slices of lemon over chicken. Bake, uncovered, in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes, turning pieces after 30 minutes.
Increase oven temperature to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and melted butter. Turn into 1 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and melted butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

Grease and lightly flour a 10-inch cake pan. In a large bowl, cream shortening and butter. Gradually add sugar, mixing until light and fluffy. Stir in the lemon and vanilla extracts and grated lemon rind. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour and baking powder and stir them into batter a little at a time alternately with warm milk. Do not overbeat. Spoon the batter into prepared pan. Bake for 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes or until the cake pulls away from the sides of the pan and a cake tester comes out clean. Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes before removing it. Cool it completely on a rack before placing it on a serving platter. It is better the 2nd day.

title: cow pie
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate and shortening.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix jello, boiling water and cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add the remaining ingredients to jello mix and chill in greased 8-inch square pan or mold.
Recipe is from the Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: kielbasa vinaigrette
directions: Poach sausage as follows:
Put sausage in an enamel or stainless steel skillet.
Cover with a mixture of 1/2 red wine and 1/2 water.
Add onion slices.
Bring to boil; cover, lower heat and cook gently for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool in poaching liquid.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Combine vegetables, water, parsley flakes, seasonings and bouillon cube.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add flour to milk until well blended.
Add to hot mixture, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and set aside to cool.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Dice green pepper and tomatoes.
Chop onion.
Mix all ingredients except taco chips.
Just before serving, crush chips and toss with salad.
Makes a big salad.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix onion, margarine and sour cream together.
Pour over potatoes.
Put cheese on top of potatoes.
Crush corn flakes and put on top.
Drizzle 1/2 stick margarine on top of potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 325° uncovered.

title: mom's never fail dumplings
directions: Add butter to boiling water.
When melted, add salt and flour; mix well.
(May need a little more flour or a little less to maintain rolling consistency.)
Put in refrigerator and chill so it will roll better.
Roll on floured board and cut into dumplings. Drop into your favorite broth and cook for about 30 minutes.

title: angel hair marinara
directions: In large skillet, heat oil; add onions, mushrooms and squash. Cook 5 minutes, stirring often. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic and oregano. Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 5 minutes.

title: cabbage marinara
directions: Cook ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in rice and seasonings.
Spread 1/2 of cabbage in greased 2-quart baking dish. Cover with meat mixture.
Then spread rest of cabbage over top. Pour undiluted soup over top.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour. Serve over additional rice.

title: microwave beef stew
directions: Stir beef, 1/4 cup flour, salt and pepper in a 3-quart casserole until beef is coated.
Add 2 1/2 cups hot water, potatoes, carrots, celery, catsup, bouquet sauce and garlic. Microwave, covered, at High (100%) for 5 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium (50%).
Microwave until beef is tender, 40 minutes to 1 hour, stirring once or twice during cooking.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour and 1/2 cup cold water until smooth.
Stir flour mixture and peas into stew; cover.
Microwave at Medium (50%) until mixture thickens slightly and peas are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and oleo well; add vanilla.
Beat in sugar, a little at a time, until of spreading consistency.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Mix cake until all ingredients are blended.
Grease and flour long pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(made with pancake batter)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Put brown sugar and butter in 9-inch glass pie plate.
Place in oven and heat 7 minutes. Stir twice until mixture is smooth and starts to bubble.
Cut pineapple slices in half.
Remove pie plate from oven and arrange pineapple and cherries on sugar mixture.
Open top of pancake batter.
Add sugar and reserved juice.
Stir to mix.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown and pick comes out clean.
Cool on rack 5 minutes before loosening edges with small knife.
Invert cake on platter.
Serve warm or cool.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add maraschino cherries and pecan pieces to taste.
Chill.

title: amish broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Slice onion thin.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix broccoli, onions, raisins and bacon. Blend mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Fold dressing into vegetable mix and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: easy lemon delight cake
directions: Slice angel food cake into 4 layers.
Mix pie filling and yogurt in bowl.
Spread between layers.
Spread whipped topping over top and side of cake.
Chill until serving time.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Crumble up graham crackers real fine.
Add melted margarine. Press into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let cool.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions on box. Then add cream cheese and spread over graham cracker crust.
Add cheese to top and enjoy.

title: no-fuss pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides over medium heat.
Place in shallow pan, side by side.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon evenly over pork chops.
Cover pan.
Bake a 350° for 1 hour, or until chops are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl, stirring to blend.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes, scraping sides of bowl frequently.
Pour into greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan on rack about 15 minutes.
Turn out on cake plate; cool completely before cutting.
Sift powdered sugar over top, if desired.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Mix meats thoroughly.
Add onion, celery and seasonings.
Add mustard, eggs and sauce.
Mix.
Soak bread crumbs in warm milk. Add to meat mixture and mix well.
Form into loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with hot tomato sauce.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add crushed bananas, gradually add the dry ingredients and sour milk and vanilla.
Then add nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350°.

title: texas hot cocoa cake
directions: Melt
margarine,
oil,	cocoa
and
water
in saucepan. Bring to	a
boil,
then cool. Sift flour and sugar in a bowl. Pour liquid over flour mixture. Beat until smooth. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: butternut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs until light and foamy in large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat in sugar, vanilla, margarine or butter Crisco until creamy. Combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture. Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in pecans at low speed. Mixture will be stiff.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is brown.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and top with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Beat eggs and add oil.
Add sugar, soda and salt, which have been sifted
with
flour.
Add
vanilla, nuts and apples. Bake in loaf or tube pan for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: mexican snack squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Place crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and up 1-inch sides to form crust.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Spread beans over crust.
In bowl, mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread over beans.
Spread onions, peppers, tomatoes and olives next.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve with salsa.
Makes 30 appetizers.

title: eskimo cookies
directions: You will also need wax paper.

title: andy piatt's meat loaf
directions: Cut onion and pepper in small pieces.
Add to ground beef. Add egg and quick oats; mix well.
Add seasonings and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper until sugar melts. Pour over drained vegetables and stir.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel
and
slice eggplant.
Cook until mushy and drain. Add and mix all ingredients (except 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup of crackers).
Put mixture in baking dish and top with remaining cheese
and
crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate toffee crescent bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread dough into an ungreased cookie sheet with fingertips.
In a saucepan, combine brown sugar and butter.
Boil one minute.
Pour evenly over dough.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 14 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Swirl as they melt with the back of a spoon.
Cool.
Yields 36 to 48 bars.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in ovensafe dish.

title: cabbage dish
directions: Put oil in frying pan.
Add apples and onions.
Fry 10 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Add water a little at a time.
Cook 10 minutes until cabbage is tender.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Add salt, pepper and butter and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix evaporated milk, water and sugar.
Cook slowly to 236°. Stir often.
Cool without stirring until lukewarm.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and butter.
Beat until smooth and pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cut when cool.

title: pink salad
directions: Whip Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip well.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Keeps well.
Rich, but real good.

title: sourdough starter and bread
directions: Place milk in a glass container and allow to stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Stir in flour and yeast.
Leave, uncovered, in a warm place for 2 to 5 days, depending on how long it takes it to bubble and sour.
If it starts to dry out, stir in enough tepid water to bring it back to the original consistency. Once it has a good sour aroma and is full of bubbles, it is ready to use.
Try to maintain about 1 1/2 cups of starter.
Each time part of the starter is used, replenish with a mixture of equal parts of milk and flour.
Leave at room temperature several hours or overnight or until it begins to fill with bubbles.
Then cover and store in refrigerator.
Starter is best if used at least once a week.
If starter isn't used for 2 or 3 weeks, spoon out and discard about half and replenish as described.
Given attention, a starter becomes more flavorful with age.
Starter can be frozen if it is not to be used for several weeks.
This will slow down yeast action and should be left at room temperature for 24 hours after thawing.

title: cheesy catfish, please!
directions: Combine the Parmesan, flour, pepper and paprika.
Dip catfish in milk and coat with cheese mixture.
Place the fish in a baking dish; pour margarine over the fish and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden and flaky.
Sprinkle fish with shredded cheese and put under broiler until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-cooked eggs in halves.
Slip out yolks.
Mash with fork.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Refill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it up lightly.
Garnish with bacon bits before serving.
Serve with salads or cold meat platters.

title: chocolate pudding torte
directions: Mix flour, butter and 1/2 cup nuts.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
Beat cheese with 10X sugar. Fold in 1 bowl Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Let stand in refrigerator for 5 minutes.
Spread over mix in pan.
Spread second bowl Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts; chill for at least 4 hours.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat and add can of corn and Ranch Style beans and taco mix.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients together.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add crushed pineapple alternately with flour mixture.
Add nuts, raisins and apples.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: uncle verne's breast of duck
directions: Place duck breast on aluminum foil.
Rub on butter and bacon. Then place the slice of bacon on top of duck.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Seal the foil tightly.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen cucumber and onion
directions: Mix.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours or freeze until needed, then thaw out.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together, put in baked pie shell.
Chill. Makes 2 pies.

title: oriental salad
directions: Heat oil in skillet; toast almonds and sesame seed until lightly browned.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Makes about ten 1/2 cup servings.

title: fat-free vegetable soup
directions: Buy small cans of everything except broth.
Broth should be 15 or 16 ounce cans.
Place broth in large heavy pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add all drained canned vegetables except tomatoes.
Cook slowly over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add celery, onion, cabbage, rice and tomatoes and continue to cook slowly in covered pot.
Flavor with seasoning (other than salt) to taste.
Add water if necessary, but cook for another hour over low heat until everything is well done and flavors are well blended. Many servings.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla. Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamy mixture; mix well. Chill dough 1 hour.
Shape chilled dough into 48 (1-inch) balls and place in lightly greased 1 3/4-inch muffin pans, shaping ball into each shell.
Bake 12 minutes at 350° (dough will raise). Remove from oven and immediately press a peanut butter cup into each hot crust.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: picnic baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in microwave for 8 minutes on High.
Let set for 5 minutes.

title: iced mint mist punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large pitcher.
Chill well and serve over cracked ice.
Makes about 12 servings.
For a larger party, double recipe and serve in a punch bowl.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and basil.
Stir in chicken broth and cook until it thickens and comes to boil.
Add chicken.
Mix cottage cheese with beaten egg. Place 1/3 of the chicken mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with 1/3 of the noodles, 1/3 of the cottage cheese, 1/3 of the spinach and 1/3 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat
layers until all ingredients are used up.
End with last 1/3 of the chicken.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: angel hair with chicken and water chestnuts
directions: In frying pan or wok, add 1 tablespoon oil. Cook chicken breast. Add soy sauce as needed. Add garlic and asparagus. Cover and let simmer on low for 15 to 20 minutes. Add water chestnuts and cook about 10 more minute. Add more soy sauce as needed for flavor. Add cooked angel hair pasta and stir.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots and raisins in a bowl.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients and pour the mixture over the salad.
Mix all this together thoroughly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove bones and skin.
Cut into pieces. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth.
Melt butter in baking dish. Add 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Layer chicken on top, then cream of chicken soup and peas.
Cover all with the rest of stuffing. (Layer ingredients; do not mix.)
Pour chicken broth over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rum fudge pudding dessert
directions: In mixing bowl, mix together 3/4 cup of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and 3 tablespoons cocoa.
Mix butter, milk and vanilla into dry ingredients, just until blended.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle top of batter with remaining 1/2 cup granulated sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Pour water and rum over.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Serve at room temperature with whipped cream or ice cream on side, if desired.

title: barbecue weenies
directions: Cut wieners into 1-inch slices.
Pour barbecue sauce over them and sprinkle with garlic.
Cook in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours.

title: banana sour cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, bananas and sour cream.
Mix well.
In another bowl, combine frosting mix, butter and oats and mix well. Pour 1/2 cake batter into long cake pan or tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of frosting mix over cake batter.
Pour remaining cake batter over frosting mix, then sprinkle remaining frosting mix over bake batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: panned cabbage
directions: Melt the butter or margarine in a heavy skillet.
Add the cabbage; cover tight and let cabbage steam over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir now and then to prevent sticking.
Season with salt and pepper.
The cabbage gives enough of its own water to make steam and will have a wonderful color and texture cooked this way. This makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato soup(originally from flossie ferch)
directions: Peel potatoes, quarter length wise, and slice thinly.
Put potatoes and onions in a 4 quart sauce pan and add water just to cover.
Add salt to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer and cook until the smallest potato slices begin to fall apart.

title: southwestern black beans and rice
directions: Bring 1 quart of water to boil in Dutch oven or large saucepan. Stir in beans and next 7 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add ham; simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Cook red and green peppers in oil until tender-crisp. Stir into rice.
Serve beans with rice.
Makes 4 servings, only 359 calories per serving and 5 grams of fat.

title: fried squash
directions: Mix well and fry in hot grease.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Stir in wet.
Add cheese and peppers.
Pour into baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: cayenne pretzels
directions: In a small bowl, combine the oil, dressing mix, garlic salt and cayenne pepper. Divide pretzels between 2 ungreased jelly roll pans. Pour mixture over pretzels; stir to coat. Bake at 200° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown, stirring occasionally. Cool completely. Store in an airtight container. YIELD: 3 1/2 quarts.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, white vinegar and sugar.
Add mayonnaise mix to vegetables; let set in refrigerator overnight to enhance flavor.

title: crock-pot macaroni pie
