directions: Cook noodles in boiling water with salt until almost done. Drain and rinse.
Slice Velveeta cheese.
In crock-pot, layer noodles, margarine and Velveeta until pot is almost full.
Mix egg with a cup of milk and pepper (to your liking); pour mixture over ingredients in crock-pot.
Add more milk until you can see it almost at the top of the ingredients in crock-pot.
Plug pot in; let the pie cook for at least 1 hour, or until milk and egg mixture thickens.
(Sometimes I add other cheeses with Velveeta for a different taste.)

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In frying pan, saute ground round with diced onion.
Drain. In large Dutch pot, add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook approximately for 1 1/2 hours.

title: parmesan and garlic tortellini
directions: Cook tortellini according to directions on package.
Mix butter with cooked tortellini until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.

title: pork marsala
directions: Heat oil on high heat.
Brown and remove pork.
Reduce to medium heat.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes.
Add garlic; cook 2 minutes.
Stir in broth.
Bring to boil and then reduce heat to simmer.
Reduce liquid by a 1/4.
Add basil, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Put pork into broth.
Add wine.
Cover and simmer until pork is tender (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Combine pineapple and cheese.
Mix together sugar and flour. Combine in casserole.
Cover with 3/4 roll crackers, crumbled. Melt butter and pour over cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: asparagus deluxe
directions: In double boiler, melt butter and cheese.
Put asparagus in casserole dish.
Pour melted butter and cheese over the asparagus. Add salt and pepper and mix all of this well.
Put crushed corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: roly-poly cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with mixer.
Add oats and mix well with hands.
Roll into small balls.
Then roll in powdered sugar. M-mm-mm Good!

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Beat until light.
Sift baking powder, flour and salt together.
Add nuts to batter. Rotate, adding part flour and part milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Put in tube cake pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix and jello; add strawberries, oil and milk, beating with mixer. Add eggs, one at a time. Fold in pecans and coconut. Bake in layer pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spareribs and kraut
directions: Season ribs with salt and pepper.
Combine kraut and liquid with remaining ingredients.
Place in Dutch oven.
Place ribs meaty side up atop kraut.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 2 1/3 to 3 1/2 hours or until ribs are done.
During last hour, baste kraut with juices.

title: depression cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square cake pan.
In medium saucepan, mix margarine, brown sugar, raisins, cinnamon, cloves, salt, nutmeg and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add flour, soda and baking powder.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pear bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, milk, and oil together. Add nuts and pears. Mix together flour, oats, baking powder, ginger, cinnamon, and salt. Mix together with pear mixture until dry ingredients are moistened. Bake in loaf pan at 350 for 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes and then remove from pan.

title: onion mushroom meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Place mixture in a large loaf pan and bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: golden glow congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and salt.
Pour in container and let congeal.
Remove from refrigerator.
Add carrots and nuts.
Return to refrigerator until firm.
Serve on lettuce.

title: seven layer ribbon jello
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water. Boil milk and strain. Add sugar, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water to each box of jello (making 1 box at a time).
Pour into 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Chill.
Then pour 1 1/2 cups white mix over jello.
Chill again.
Repeat jello and white mixture and chill between each layer, end with cherry jello on top.

title: bran muffins
directions: *I use milk, add 2 teaspoons of lemon juice and let set for 5 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add powdered sugar.
Stir well and add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Shape into crescent balls and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spiced baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In shallow baking dish, combine sugar, flour and cinnamon. Mix well. Peel and partially core apples, leaving bottom of apples intact. Dip apples in melted butter. Roll in sugar mixture. Reserve remaining butter and sugar mixture. Place apples in shallow baking dish. Combine walnuts, remaining butter and remaining sugar mixture. Spoon into cavities of apples. Add water to baking dish to just cover bottom. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: eggplant and beef casserole
directions: Peel and boil diced eggplants.
Saute meat, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Soak bread in egg and milk mixture.
Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dan and vicki's chicken
directions: Cut up chicken breast.
Roll in eggs and bread crumbs.
Brown in oiled pan.
Put chicken in a casserole dish.

title: swedish slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, bell pepper and onion and mix together.
Then in separate pan, mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt and turmeric and bring to a boil.
Let boil for 2 minutes, then pour over cabbage, bell pepper and onion mixture.
Mix good.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.

title: scalloped hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix together hash browns, sour cream, Velveeta, softened butter or margarine, soup and onion; mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix corn flakes and melted margarine.
Put on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion.
Drain.
Add Prego sauce and mix well.
Heat about 15 minutes over medium heat.
Cook lasagna noodles until almost done.
Layer noodles, meat sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use a large, oblong Pyrex dish.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, sugar and cocoa. Set aside. Boil water, oil and butter and add to flour mixture. Add buttermilk, soda and eggs to flour mixture. Mix well. Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan, greased and floured. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet; take fork and press down on all sides.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(Check on them at 8 minutes.) When they start to brown on bottom, they are ready.

title: pie crust for lemon meringue
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and then add 2 tablespoons milk. Bake 10 minutes at 425° after pressing in pie tin.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.	Add potatoes, oil and water. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix.
Stir in pecans and raisins. Pour into loaf pans (about 2 x 6-inch aluminum pans, sprayed with Pam cooking spray).
Cook for one hour.
This will make 6 small loaf pans.

title: blueberry cheese pancakes
directions: Sift four, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a medium bowl.
Stir in sugar and wheat germ; set aside.
Combine milk, cottage cheese, egg and oil in a small bowl.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Boil real good.
Cook 5 minutes or longer.
Remove from heat and beat well.
Makes real good icing.

title: texas meat loaf
directions: Salt and pepper hamburger meat in large bowl.
In separate bowl, mix chopped onion, crackers, tomato sauce, egg, garlic, parsley and milk.
Slice bell pepper into rings; put aside 3 rings. Chop remaining pepper and add to other ingredients.
Mix both bowls of ingredients together by hand; place into loaf pan.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove, spread catsup on top and place 3 pepper rings as garnish.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: garnet and gold salad
directions: Mix the gelatin, boiling water and crushed pineapple in a bowl. Pour into a mold. Chill until partially set. Add the sour cream and mix well. Chill until set. Top with twists of the pineapple slices. Makes 8 servings.

title: corn relish
directions: Drop corn in boiling water and boil 5 minutes.
Dip in cold water.
Cut from cob.
Combine all ingredients and boil 15 minutes.
Pack in jars and process 15 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 pints.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in melted chocolate and zucchini. Add dry ingredients. Stir in chips.
Bake in 2 very well-greased pans at 350° for almost 1 hour.

title: fake crab cakes
directions: Mix together in a skillet with oil.
Brown on both sides. Tastes just like crab cakes.

title: easy french bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from beans and chestnuts.
Layer them in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Mix soup and seasonings and pour over mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with onion rings; bake about 10 minutes more.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Whisk soups, mayonnaise, lemon and curry in medium bowl. Put broccoli in bottom of pan.
Top with chicken.
Pour soup mixture over all and top with cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly and lightly browned.
Scatter onions over top.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes more.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Saute onion in butter until golden; set aside in a medium bowl. Mix eggs and milk until blended.
Add corn and muffin mix; mix well.
Spread corn batter into preheated baking dish.
Spoon sauteed onion over top and spread sour cream over onion.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 35 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serves 16.

title: low-fat pizzas
directions: Brown English muffin halves sprinkled with garlic salt under broiler.
Spread halves with spaghetti sauce.
Steam onion and green pepper in small amount of water in microwave.
Brown sausage in skillet, breaking up meat.
Add sausage, peppers, onion and cheese to taste atop the English muffin halves.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: wrapped pickles
directions: Spread some cream cheese onto one slice of beef.
Place one pickle on edge of beef and cream cheese and wrap.
Slice wrapped pickle in bite size slices.
Repeat with entire pkg. of beef.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and baste roasting chicken and/or parts every 10 to 15 minutes.
(If altering recipe amounts, remember water and oil must be in equal amounts.)

title: brownies
directions: Sift together into large bowl the flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add mixture of oleo, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for about 35 minutes.
Cut in squares and remove from pan while warm.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and make into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place asparagus in baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup, water, salt and pepper. Pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake 45 minutes in a 300° oven.
Serves 8.

title: terrie's hamburger quickie
directions: Fry hamburger and sausage until crumbly.
Drain and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: decaffeinated coffee
directions: Put coffee in a large bowl.
Pour water over grounds and leave in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Strain liquid through paper towels and discard grounds.
Put "essence of coffee" liquid in a cup of boiling water to taste.
Keep liquid in refrigerator.

title: impossible chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inch.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Simmer hamburger meat until done; drain.
Combine the tomatoes, soups, chilies and sauce in a saucepan and simmer until flavors are blended.

title: chess pie
directions: Put pie shell in oven 5 to 10 minutes to get part of moisture out.
Melt margarine and add sugar.
Beat eggs and add to cooled butter and sugar.
Add vinegar, meal and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
If pie shakes in the middle, cook 5 or 10 minutes longer.

title: italian broccoli
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a pan and heat.
Drain the broccoli and put it in a serving bowl.
Pour the sauce over the broccoli and sprinkle with cheese.

title: 7 step venison jerky
directions: Slice venison into slices about 3/4-inch thick.
In a container combine the remaining ingredients.
Stir well to dissolve.
Place venison strips into the marinade, making sure that all the venison is covered.
Marinate overnight, turning if necessary.
Lay marinated strips on oven rack.
Cook 6 to 8 hours at 150°.
They get crisper the longer that they bake.
Store in an airtight container; it will keep up to two years.

title: homemade fudge sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan stir together sugar, cocoa and cinnamon. Add cream and milk, mix well.
Over medium heat, bring to boil stirring constantly.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool 15 minutes.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Stir in vanilla. Store covered in refrigerator. Stir before serving.

title: five-hour stew
directions: Combine and bake at 250° for 5 hours in covered roaster-Dutch oven.
Do not remove lid until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Cook over medium heat; boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; stir well.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal, mixing well. Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: bacon appetizer crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese, bacon, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley and milk in a small bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In buttered 9 x 13-inch dish, put hash browns.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over potatoes.
In a bowl, mix onions, soup, sour cream and Cheez Whiz.
Spread on potatoes.
It will fill the dish.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain beans and put into slow cooker.
Brown hamburger; drain grease and add to beans.
Fry bacon and cut into 1/2-inch strips. Mix into beans.
Mix in rest of ingredients and cook on medium heat 1 1/2 hours.

title: party turnovers
directions: In a medium skillet
combine
meat and soup mix.
Brown well and drain off fat.
Fold in cheese;
set aside.
Separate rolls according to package directions.
Then cut the triangles in halves.
Place spoonful of
meat
mixture in center of each triangle;
fold
over and
seal
edges.
Place
on
ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: prune bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 1 cup of bran; cool.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs. Stir in buttermilk, soaked bran, remaining bran, dry ingredients and prunes.
Mix well.
Pour in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Batter keeps well in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: seafood quiche(dee-licious)
directions: Cut Swiss cheese into finger-length pieces, 1/4-inch wide. Cover bottom and sides of pastry shell.
Combine cream, eggs, flour, salt, pepper, nutmeg and cayenne to taste.
Stir in melted butter and sherry.
Beat everything together until well blended. Pour about 2/3 of mixture into pastry shell.
Put crab meat and shrimp into mixture in shell carefully, pushing it down with a fork so that custard mixture covers it well.
Pour rest of custard mixture into shell (after you have it on oven rack to keep it from spilling).
Bake in 375° oven approximately 40 minutes or until browned on top.
Do let stand at least 20 minutes before serving.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine refried beans and taco seasoning.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer the rest of the ingredients in the order listed.
Makes 6 cups.
Use nachos, corn chips, potato chips, etc. to dip.

title: hobo beans
directions: Mix beans together. Brown hamburg with medium diced onions. Drain grease. Pour over beans. Mix vinegar, brown mustard, brown sugar and ketchup. Pour over beans and hamburg. Mix all together. Sprinkle with bacon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jackpot casserole
directions: Saute ground round, green pepper and onion.
Cook noodles; drain.
Add corn, soup, tomato sauce, chili and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a casserole
and top generously with grated cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: almond tea
directions: Simmer sugar, water and lemon juice 5 minutes, then cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
May be served hot or cold.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs, when done peel eggs and cut into half long ways. Take out egg yolks and place in bowl, add kraft sandwich spread, salt, and pepper.
Mix well.
After mixture is creamy and smooth, using teaspoon place small amount back into egg halves, chill and serve when desired.

title: blue ribbon chocolate chips
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl, with an electric mixer, blend sugars at medium speed.
Add butter and mix to form a grainy paste, scaping down the sides of the bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla extract; mix at medium speed until fully combined.
Do not overmix.
Add the flour mixture and chocolate chips.
Blend at low speed.
Don't overmix.

title: butter toffee
directions: Melt butter, add sugar and water; cook, stirring constantly, until candy thermometer reaches 340°.
I use a large heavy aluminum pan and stir with a long handled rubber spatula.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan or better yet a heavy aluminum pancake griddle.
Let cool a few minutes and then break the Hershey bars over top.
Let it melt a minute and spread over top.
Sprinkle with 2 cups ground or chopped nuts.
(I usually use pecans, however, cashews or whatever are delicious too.)
Press nuts down into chocolate a bit.
Let cool and cut by breaking pieces off.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
In a paper bag, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Shake biscuit quarters in bag.
Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Put a little of the syrup in the bottom of a Bundt pan and add a few nuts.
Put a layer of syrup and then a layer of biscuit quarters back and forth.
Makes about 3 layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and serve.
You just pull it apart.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and whipping cream alternately.
Begin and end with flour.
Bake at 300° until done, approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: pancho villa(7-layer dip)
directions: In a 9 X 13 inch pan, layer each ingredient in the order given.
Chill overnight.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: no bake butterballs
directions: Mix well.
Form balls the size of walnuts and refrigerate.
Or, if dough is too sticky, refrigerate first and then form the balls.

title: skillet sweet potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Melt margarine in skillet and cook the potato slices until golden. Reduce heat, cover and cook until done.
Add the pineapple juice if potatoes tend to stick.
Add the crushed pineapple and syrup and cook until thick and potatoes are cooked to desired doneness.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, mix first 4 ingredients. Stir in milk, oleo and nuts.
Pour batter into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Sprinkle over batter in pan.
Pour hot water on batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 45 minutes.
Can be served warm or cold.
Invert onto dessert plate and spoon sauce over each square of cake.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on HIGH for 3 minutes. Stir until smooth. Add vanilla and nuts. Cool; cut into squares.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados until almost smooth (leave a few lumps).
If the fruit is hard place it in paper bag for several days - if they are too soft, place in refrigerator.
It will take some efforts to stay on top of this item.
Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator overnight to allow flavors to blend.

title: mostaccioli and sausage bake
directions: Brown sausage.
Add sausage, noodles and Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Top with Mozzarella cheese before baking.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: layered tortilla pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf - barbecue style
directions: Mix and pour over meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Baste occasionally; cover with foil while cooking.
Remove cover about 10 minutes before done to let brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Put in crock-pot; add all other ingredients.
Cook 2 or 3 hours.

title: bride's salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Let sit in refrigerator until thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Pour in a mold or pan to gel.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread and mix with chopped vegetables.
Mix remaining ingredients and stir into salad prior to serving.

title: fudge drops
directions: Over hot (not boiling) water, melt morsels.
Remove from heat. Stir in cereal and peanuts.
Drop by rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper lined cookie sheets.
Garnish with whole nuts, if desired.
Chill in refrigerator until firm, about 30 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello as direction gives.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Mix cream cheese and food coloring together in separate bowl and then add to jello.
Add drained pineapple and Cool Whip and nuts, if desired.
Then mix all ingredients together on slow speed and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.

title: carrot stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook 30 minutes, then simmer for 5 minutes before adding 1/4 cup skim milk and 1/4 tablespoon flour for thickness.
You may eat with crackers or cornbread when served.

title: corn and cherry tomato salad
directions: Combine the yogurt, ketchup and mustard in a large bowl.
Stir in the green onions and dill and set aside.
Bring 2 cups water to boil in small saucepan.
Add the corn and cook for 45 seconds or until tender.
Drain in a colander.
Rinse under cold, running water to stop the cooking and drain again.
Add the dressing along with cherry tomatoes and green peppers and toss well to mix. Place lettuce on plates and spoon corn mixture on top.
Serves 4.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into pieces for serving.
Place in a casserole dish. Cover.
Bake the ribs in an oven at 500° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 150°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, melt the margarine.
Stir in the raw rice.
Beat out the lumps in the soup before mixing it with water. Pour half of the soup mix over the rice.
Place the chicken on the rice and pour the remainder of the soup mix over it.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Mix and refrigerate several hours.
Serve with carrots, cauliflower, celery, turnips, etc.

title: elegant stuffed mushrooms
directions: Carefully wash mushrooms; remove the stems, set aside.	Finely dice about half of the stems and place into mixing bowl (you may discard the other half, or use as an ingredient in spaghetti sauce, etc.); and add sour cream, cheeses, and bread crumbs blend well. Fill mushrooms caps with filling mixture, mounding tops.
Drizzle melted butter over stuffed mushrooms; if desired, sprinkle top with additional mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted on top or golden brown.

title: orange-mince ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart ring mold; sprinkle walnuts over bottom.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a large bowl.
Stir lightly with fork to mix.
Beat eggs until blended in a medium size bowl; stir in salad oil, mincemeat and orange rind.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir until mixture is evenly moist.
Spoon over walnuts in mold; level top. Bake 45 minutes or until golden and a cake tester inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool loaf in mold on wire rack 10 minutes; turn out onto rack and cool.
For easy, neat slicing, wrap loaf tightly in transparent wrap or foil and let stand overnight.
Yield:
1 eight-inch ring.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Split layers and put frosting in between and on top of layers. Place in cake container and refrigerate for 3 days before using. Keep refrigerated.
Also freezes well.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt
margarine,
peanut
butter
and
chocolate chips. Stir until
smooth.
Pour over Crispix and stir.
Let cool for a while. Put
cups
powdered
sugar (you may want more) in brown bag. Put Crispix in bag and shake! Shake! Shake!

title: liver and onions
directions: Dredge liver with seasoned flour; saute in hot fat until slightly brown.
Place in greased baking dish.
Cover with onions. Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Add 1/2 cup hot water; cover.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes, adding more water, if needed.
Remove cover; bake 10 minutes longer.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli only 5 minutes; drain.
Pour in greased 2-quart dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix soup and milk; pour over cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove.
Top with onion rings. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes longer or until onions are crisp and brown.

title: pecan whiskey cake
directions: Line three loaf pans with aluminum foil.
Set the oven at 250°.
Separate 6 eggs.
Beat the whites until they stand in soft peaks.
Beat in sugar.
Without washing the beater, beat yolks until thick; set aside.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, butter and egg.
Mix just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin pan or use paper cups.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix coconut and nuts. Sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Make cake mix by directions.
Pour over nuts.
Mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Stir slightly for marble effect.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: peek-a-boo
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add vanilla and flour, little at a time, mixing well.
Take 3/4 of batter and spread on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Make sure dough is extended up sides of cookie sheet.
Spread pie filling over layer.
Drop the remaining batter by spoonfuls over the filling and spread.
Be sure to leave parts of pie filling uncovered so it gives a peek-a-boo effect.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter toast
directions: Cook in double boiler for 3 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Saute apple until tender (in microwave) about 14 minutes. Then add butter, sugar, eggs, flour, whiskey, salt, soda, cinnamon, raisins, fruits and pecans.
Put in baking pan. Decorate top with pineapple, cherries and whole pecans.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into a 11 x 7 inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Serve with chunky salsa if desired.

title: coffee roll
directions: Roll biscuits in margarine, then in mixture of sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pack into round cake pan (standing up).
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place lettuce in a bowl.
Cover with onions, pepper and celery.
Spread layer of mayonnaise over this.
Sprinkle with sugar, cheese and bacon crumbs.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: new england brown bread
directions: Mix ingredients and place in greased container.
Steam 3 hours.
Never fails!

title: ernie's apricot salad
directions: Drain the apricots and reserve the syrup plus 6 of the apricot halves.
Cut the remaining apricots in half.
Combine salad dressing, honey, 2 tablespoons syrup and halved apricots.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan and freeze.
When frozen, arrange halved apricots on top.
Garnish with maraschino cherry halves.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in large mixing bowl. Beat well. Set aside. Mix sliced apples, cinnamon and sugar together until well coated. Alternate layers of batter and layers of apples in a greased and floured tube pan, beginning with batter and ending with apples. Do not preheat oven. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate decandence pie
directions: Line spring-form pan with split ice cream sandwiches, cookie side down.
Top with 1 quart of ice cream.
Top with chocolate sauce and nuts.
Top with 1 quart ice cream, then top with more chocolate sauce and nuts.
Freeze overnight.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: lesueur pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese (generously).
Make topping with 1 stick margarine (melted); mix with 1 roll of Ritz crackers (crushed).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and crumble 1/2 of cake into punch bowl.
Layer 1/2 of the pineapple, 1/2 of the pudding and pie filling, 1/2 of the cherry pie filling and half of the Cool Whip.
Top with nuts. Repeat once.

title: cheesy cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine or butter in kettle. Saut onions, carrots and celery until tender.

Add the flour and blend until mixture looks golden. Slowly add the milk; stir until there are no lumps. Add broth, cheese and broccoli pieces. Cook on simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender. If you wish, you may use uncooked broccoli pieces and simmer for 1 hour or so until broccoli is tender.

title: chess cake
directions: Make first layer by melting butter and cooling.
Add eggs, then cake mix.
Mix together and spread in greased and floured oblong pan.
Make second layer by mixing remaining 4 ingredients together.
Spread over the first layer.
Bake about 1 hour at 325°.
Cut into squares.
Will have chewy consistency.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 c. pudding into a 2 1/2 qt. glass serving bowl.
Top with one-third of the wafers, one-third of the bananas, and one-third of the pudding.
Repeat layers two more times, ending with pudding on top. Chill and garnish as desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour over popped corn in two 13 x 9-inch pans.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs until light. Spoon flour (not sifted) into dry measuring cup; level off and pour flour onto waxed paper. Add soda and salt together (not sifted). Stir to blend. Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with mashed bananas and lemon juice. Stir until all ingredients are moistened. Stir in nuts. Spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pan immediately. Cool on rack.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low for 1 to 2 hours.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients with wire whisk or hand mixer until smooth.
Pour scant 1/4 cup onto hot griddle (grease, if needed). Makes about 18 (4-inch) pancakes.
For no cholesterol, substitute skim milk for whole milk and 2 egg whites or 1/4 cup egg product for the egg.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together sugar and eggs.
Add Wesson oil, mixing well.
Add soda, salt and cinnamon, then flour, mixing well.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: rum punch
directions: Mix all but ginger ale and rum; add these 2 ingredients at serving time.

title: my mama's buttermilk pie
directions: In double boiler, boil milk, eggs, sugar and butter.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Place in a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Saute onions.
Add bacon and eggs (previously cooked).
Reduce heat.
Add shrimp to onions and bacon mixture and cook until shrimp turn pink.
Mix in cooked rice.
Lightly coat with soy sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 generous servings.

title: old fashioned potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery and water.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until done.
Put vegetables through a coarse sieve, and return to water in which they were cooked.
Add milk, salt and pepper; reheat.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Just before serving, float parsley and crisp bacon pieces on soup.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Combine onion and garlic with 3 tablespoons of the water; set aside for 10 minutes to soften.
In a large skillet, heat oil until hot.
Add softened onion and garlic; saute until lightly browned, about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, green peppers, zucchini, chili powder, salt, oregano, cumin and black pepper. Simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.

title: meat and spinach casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and beef in a wide frying pan; cook until meat loses pink color.
Add onion and garlic, cook, stirring occasionally, or until soft but not brown.	Blend in liquid ingredients and spices; simmer slowly, uncovered, until reduced to about 6 cups (about 30 minutes).

title: speedy caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Blend in brown sugar and salt.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk; continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Blend in confectioners sugar gradually.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Frosts 8 or 9-inch layer cake.

title: quick chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken until it is no longer pink (just a few minutes). Cut into chunks.
Take broccoli and cut into quarters.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Place chicken over broccoli.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain grease.
Mix the rest of ingredients together and add to bacon.
Bring to a boil.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook and cool pie shell.
In large pot, mix cornstarch and sugar, then heat, adding water a little at a time, then add food coloring.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes (until thickens).
Remove from heat and stir longer.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add strawberries to mixture when cooled down (not cold).
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before eating.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Place strawberries in a dish to thaw a little.
Mash banana.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Mash strawberries a little.
Add banana, pineapple and nuts to Jell-O.
Place 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13 dish or mold and place in refrigerator to set until firm enough to spread sour cream over the top (about 15 minutes).
Remove and cover with sour cream.
Top with remaining 1/2 of Jell-O mixture and place in refrigerator to chill.

title: firehouse rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
In second bowl, add next 3 ingredients.
When yeast is dissolved, pour second mix into flour mixture, stirring until well blended.
Set in warm place until dough rises to double in size.
Pour onto floured sheet; knead and make into small balls.
Put on greased baking sheets.
These may be frozen at this stage, before being allowed to rise again.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: marissa's ambrosia supreme
directions: Mix together the marshmallows, pineapple chunks, shredded coconut and mandarin oranges.
Slowly stir in sour cream until well blended.
Walnuts may be added, if desired.

title: "jail chili"
directions: Put meat and seasonings in heavy kettle.
Cook under cover slowly for 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add a little water and cook another hour.

title: singapore chicken satay
directions: In a small bowl, stir together curry powder, sugar, oil, soy sauce and garlic.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Fry chicken with salt, garlic and paprika.
Cook rice.
Mix onion, green pepper, parsley, tomatoes and chili powder.
Mix this with rice.

title: scallops a la dorothy
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and garlic in margarine in skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add wine, lemon pepper, thyme, parsley and salt; mix well.
Bring to a simmer.
Add scallops.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently; do not overcook.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: easy barbecue wieners
directions: Put jelly and barbecue sauce into saucepan over medium heat until well blended. Cut each wiener into 3 pieces and add to sauce. Cook until hot.

title: ever-ready bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Nabisco Bran.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, buttermilk and soaked bran.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add Kellogg's Bran.
Stir until moist.
Bake in muffin pans for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: cocoa-peanut butter mounds
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add butter and milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats, peanut butter, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool thoroughly before serving or storing.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: susie's oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and quick oatmeal mix; let cool.
Cream the sugar, brown sugar and Crisco all together.
Add the eggs; beat well.
Add to the oatmeal mixture and mix.
In a separate bowl, mix thoroughly the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Sift all together and add to the mixture.
Bake in an 8 x 14-inch pan in moderate oven.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine shortening and sugar and cream well.
Blend in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well and add pecans, dates and cherries.
Mix well and shape into balls using a level tablespoonful for each cookie.
Crush corn flakes.
Roll each ball of dough in corn flakes.
Place on greased baking sheet and top each cookie with 1/4 cherry.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bishop bread
directions: Separate eggs; beat egg yolks until light and lemon-colored. Add sugar to egg yolks gradually beating it in.
Add dry ingredients; sift together and add anise flavoring.
Fold in egg whites beaten until stiff but not dry.
Turn into a greased shallow pan and bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: oil dressing for slaw
directions: Mix in small bowl until thick.

title: brewster's chili
directions: Cover meat with water; mix well and let boil 1 hour.
Add all other ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Cook slowly another hour.
Add cracker crumbs and let boil 5 or 10 minutes more.
I half this.
It will freeze.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Cook over low heat, stir constantly until thick and clear.
Stir small amount of mixture into egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture and continue stirring and cooking for 1 minute.
Add the butter, lemon juice and grated lemon peel.
Blend thoroughly and serve warm.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, sugars and 2/3 of the Cool Whip.
Spread over cool crust.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Spoon over cream cheese layer and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of pecans over the top. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: play dough
directions: Combine ingredients and mix until dough forms.
Roll and cut as desired.
Store in airtight container.
Will last a good while if kept airtight.

title: celery sticks
directions: Cut celery stalks in half. Spread with peanut butter; sprinkle with raisins. Enjoy.

title: kentucky dried apple pies
directions: Soak dried apples in water to cover apples.
Should plump up to nearly same size as when fresh.
Simmer in same water until tender. Sweeten to taste and add cinnamon if desired.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil. Mix all dry ingredients bran, flour soda, salt. Add alternately butter milk and dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Add flavoring last. Dough can be stored in refrigerator indefinitely and cooked when desired.
Makes umpteen dozen.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: butter brickle bread
directions: Beat 3 minutes.
Pour and bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
To use coffee cans, grease well only and fill 1/2 full.
Then bake.

title: helen's baked beans plus
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in 9X13 inch dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: seedless jam cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks, jam and pineapple to the creamed mixture.
Blend until smooth. Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with the buttermilk to the creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites and nuts into the batter.
Bake in three small 8-inch layer pans at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spread with Caramel Icing.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Mix coconut and nuts and spread into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Pour mixed cake mix over coconut and nuts.
Melt cream cheese and margarine; mix into powdered sugar and pour this over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Melt marshmallows on top of double boiler with milk until dissolved.
Beat out lumps with spoon.
Cool to room temperature. Whip the Dream Whip or cream.
Add cream, drained pineapple and vanilla (if cream was used) to mixture.
Crush crackers fine. Place half of them in bottom of medium sized cake pan and pour in pineapple mixture; then top with remaining 1/2 of crushed crackers.
Chill 6 to 12 hours (this will give pineapple chance to flavor the mixture).

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into size of a walnut.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: caramel-pecan pie
directions: Place 1 cup pecans in bottom of pastry shell; drizzle with 1/4 cup caramel topping.
Set aside.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown and drain beef; set aside.
Cut cheese into cubes and melt in large bowl in microwave, stirring after each minute or two.
Drain tomatoes; reserve liquid.
Add tomatoes and beef to cheese.
Add a little liquid if needed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in saucepan until almost tender.
Meanwhile, combine the remaining ingredients in the blender until smooth and creamy.
Place cooked potatoes in baking dish; pour sauce over them and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix with 3 eggs (will be dry and crumbly).
Add cherry pie filling.
Mix well.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until done.
Save broth from chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with dressing mix, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and chicken broth.
Tear up chicken in small pieces.
In casserole dish, put a layer of mixture, then a layer of chicken, then a top layer of mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad for mayonnaise haters
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and cool. Once cooled thoroughly, add all other ingredients.
Refrigerate. Salad dressing may dry out and you may want to add a little more just before serving.
Makes about 15 servings.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; remove from heat.
Add flour and stir until lumps are gone.
Cut up cheese.
Add cheese and milk to flour and butter mixture in skillet.
Stir constantly until cheese melts and a thick sauce is formed.
Pour over boiled, drained chunks of potatoes in a casserole dish.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in a 350° oven until it bubbles, about 10 or 15 minutes.

title: fried asparagus
directions: Drain asparagus.
Roll in crumbs and dip in slightly beaten egg.
Roll in crumbs again and fry in deep fat about 5 minutes. No. 2 1/2 can serves 6.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cornmeal, baking powder and salt together. Add eggs, oil and corn; mix well by hand.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil until golden brown.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator.
Can be made into smaller quantities.

title: dorothy's fruit curry
directions: Layer fruit
in a 9 x 2 x 13-inch casserole.
Melt oleo and add
curry and sugar, mixing well.	Pour over fruit.
Bake 1 1/2 hours
Refrigerate overnight and heat at 350° to serve.

title: green beans and mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for the onion rings. Grease casserole and fill with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with onion rings and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: alabama pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar until well blended. Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add flour alternately with cream, beginning and ending with flour. Continue beating and add almond extract and vanilla.
Spray a 10-inch angel food cake pan with Baker's Joy (the baking spray). Spoon in batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours or until cake is a light golden brown color on top.

title: taco salad
directions: Keep first 4 ingredients chilled.
When you are ready to serve, add Doritos, dressing and cheese.
Toss and serve.

title: grape-nut custard pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Scald milk.
Add Grape-Nuts and set aside.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla and stir.
Dot top with butter.
Bake 1/2 hour.
Test after it bubbles slightly.
Tester should be clean after inserted.

title: rhubarb surprise
directions: Mix dry white sugar and dry Jell-O in a small bowl.
Sprinkle sugar and dry Jell-O over raw rhubarb.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the sugar and Jell-O mixture in baking pan.
Pour or mix the melted oleo with the water and drizzle over the dry ingredients in your baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Works best for me in Pyrex, 9 3/4 x 6 x 2-inch.
Serve with ice cream or plain cream.

title: peanut butter ice cream sauce
directions: Combine
brown sugar, milk, Karo and butter in a saucepan. Cook
on
medium
heat;
stirring until sugar dissolves. Remove from
heat;
add
peanut butter, beating until smooth. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine and seasonings.
Layer vegetables in casserole dish (round dish).
Top with mushroom mixture. Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(Frozen vegetables may also be used.)

title: creamy alfredo sauce
directions: In medium saucepan over medium-low heat, melt butter.
Add cream.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Stir in cheese, pepper and nutmeg.
Serve over hot cooked pasta.
Makes about 1 cup sauce.

title: amazin raisin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix in order given.
Grease and flour layer cake pans.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cool and put together with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly; add eggs, pumpkin and water and mix. Sift together dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture. Stir in nuts and raisins (or dates) and bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix well. Serves 40 persons.
Fruit will float.

title: bean soup
directions: Fry hamburger with celery and onion until done. Add rest of ingredients. Let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or longer if needed.

title: spanish rice
directions: Wash rice, add other ingredients in a baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven until done and stir two times.

title: dill crackers
directions: Place crackers in a large container (loosely). Mix the oil, dressing and dill together. Pour mixture over the crackers. Cover and roll or gently shake the crackers until no oil runs from the sides of the container. Take out and put in a storage container and keep tightly covered.

title: orange surprise
directions: Use Jell-O dry.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: pear cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add pears and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in well-greased and floured pan.

title: broccoli or cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Chop cauliflower; cook and drain.
Heat milk, chicken bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cheese as liquid heats.
Saute onions in butter.
Add flour and stir until thick.
Combine liquids and cook until thick.
Add cauliflower last and heat to boil.

title: black forest cherry cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in almonds, 3/4 cup chopped chocolate and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into butter mixture.
Divide evenly between 3 greased and waxed paper-lined and regreased 8-inch layer cake pans.
Bake about 20 minutes in a moderately hot 375° oven or until edges start to pull away from sides.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Turn out; remove waxed paper.
Cool cake layers on rack. Whip the cream with honey until stiff.
Place one cake layer on serving plate; sprinkle with 1/3 of liqueur.
Spread with 1/3 of whipping cream.
Cover evenly with 1/2 sour cherries.
Place 2nd layer on top; press down slightly.
Repeat as for first layer.
Top with 3rd layer; press down slightly.
Sprinkle with liqueur.
Cover with whipped cream.
Decorate top and sides with reserved 1/4 cup chocolate and maraschino cherries.
Chill well before serving. Makes one 8-inch layer cake.

title: duke fitness center chili(with or without beans)
directions: Brown meats in Dutch oven.
Remove and place in colander.
Run very hot water through meat to remove fat.
Drain.

title: lemon squares
directions: Squeeze lemon juice (as needed).
Mix and frost.
(Doubled, this recipe will fit in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.)

title: chicago style spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain excess moisture.
Set aside.
Chop cheese and artichoke hearts in food processor.
Add spinach and sauce mix.
Blend well.
Place in casserole dish.
Microwave 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips and picante sauce.

title: peach jam(microwave)
directions: Mash peaches with potato masher. Combine with pectin, lemon juice and mace in 2-quart deep dish.
Cover and cook on High 2 minutes. Stir.
Cover and cook 3 to 4 minutes more. Cool 10 minutes. Stir in Equal.
Pour into containers.
Cover and freeze. Thaw in refrigerator. Store 1 year in freezer or 1 month in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups.
(Contains 5 calories per 1 tablespoon.)

title: annie maes fruit cake
directions: Shell nuts and set aside.
Place a package of graham crackers in a large Ziploc bag.
Roll with dough roller.
Add crackers until the whole box has been turned into crumbs.
Set aside.
Melt marshmallows in hot water.
In a large mixing bowl blend marshmallow mixture with graham cracker crumbs.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Line an angel food or Bundt pan with waxed paper.
Press cake firmly into pan.
Cover with waxed paper. Put in refrigerator for about a week.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter the pan; add crushed pineapple with the juice and add pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Cut the oleo into small pieces and layer on top.
Add pecans and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel banana cream-puff ring
directions: Combine water, margarine, sugar and salt in saucepan; bring to boil.
Add flour; stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat; add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition.
Spoon dough onto a greased cookie sheet to form a ring 7-inches diameter.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until deep golden brown and crusty.
Cool. Cut in half horizontally.
Prepare mix as directed for pudding on package except using 1 1/2 cups milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Cover surface of pudding mixture with waxed paper or transparent wrap; chill.
Fold in whipped cream and bananas.
Spread mixture over bottom half of ring.
Top with other half of ring.
Melt caramels with water in pan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Serve with ring.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: t p & l yams
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
While hot, add topping.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and flour; mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan at 325° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top while hot.
When slightly cooled, cut into squares.

title: santa's thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour and salt; mix well. Form 1-inch balls; roll in nuts.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press centers with thumb; fill with preserves.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown. Remove to wire rack; cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: eggplant-hamburg parmigiana
directions: With fork, mix beef, pepper and onion salt.
Brown mixture in skillet in 2 tablespoons salad oil on medium heat.
Drain fat and set aside.
Peel eggplant and slice into 8 slices, 3/4-inch thick. Drain on paper towels.
Combine flour, pepper and salt.
Coat eggplant in flour mixture.
Brown in 1/4 cup salad oil.
Alternate 1/2 of eggplant and 1/2 ground beef mixture in 9 x 12-inch dish. Cover with 1/2 can tomato sauce and 1/2 cup grated cheese. Sprinkle with oregano.
Put rest of eggplant and ground beef in casserole.
Cover with rest of tomato sauce and cheese.
Garnish with snipped parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan chicken
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Set aside.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into meat ball size balls. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: pennsylvania dutch bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon.
Add to eggs balance of ingredients; mix.
Add to bacon and fat.
Cook over low heat, stirring only occasionally, until of a custard consistency.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs together. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Don't overbeat. Put into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers.
Cook peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes. Cook beef and onion in skillet until light brown; drain.
Stir in rice, salt, garlic salt and 1 cup tomato sauce.
Heat through. Stuff each pepper with beef mixture; stand upright in ungreased baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Pour remaining sauce over peppers. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: black olive avocado dip
directions: Stir all together and chill.
Serve with tortillas.
Great with all Mexican foods.

title: barbara's buttermilk pound cake
directions: 1. Sift flour and baking powder together and set aside.

title: utterly deadly southern pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together two to three minutes.
Beat eggs not too stiff.
Pour in slowly the hot syrup.
Add the butter, vanilla and the pecan meats, broken rather coarsely.
Turn into a raw pie shell and bake in a moderate oven about 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large bowl, crush Doritos.
Shred lettuce.
Mix in bowl. Add chopped tomato and cheese.
Add Catalina salad dressing to taste.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: fudge microwave
directions: Put powdered sugar, peanut butter, oleo and milk in microwave bowl.
Cook on High for 1 minute.
Remove.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
Put in 8-inch square pan and refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grate potatoes in baking dish.
Melt butter and Cheddar cheese in saucepan.
Then add sour cream and chopped onion.
Put in potatoes; dot with butter, paprika and extra cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bagel-cake
directions: Slice a bagel down the middle (save the other half bagel for a duplicate recipe or whatever).
Rinse strawberries and slice just enough to make 1 cup.
Place 1/2 bagel in small bowl or dish.
Top bagel with fresh sliced strawberries.
Top with yogurt.
Enjoy, but use knife and fork since bagel is usually hard.

title: cashew chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken with celery, grapes and cashews.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Fold into chicken mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Garnish with parsley and additional cashews.
Toasted almonds may be used in place of cashews.

title: all-in-one casserole
directions: Place cabbage in a greased baking dish.
Brown beef and onion. Stir in rice and place mixture on cabbage.
Season.
Combine soup and water; pour into dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: anise cookies(biscottin)
directions: Mix sugar, salt and eggs.
Add butter, vanilla, lemon and anise; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and mix so you can handle it.
Will be soft.
Make a circle and join.
Looks like a Q.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 or 15 minutes.
Watch not to brown. Can also be rolled and cut with a glass.
May make glazed frosting.

title: hopscotch sauce
directions: Melt butter in a medium-size saucepan.
Add brown sugar, salt and syrup.
Bring to a boil and cook, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Gradually add cream, stirring constantly.
Bring to a second boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Stir in pecans.
Serve over ice cream.

title: cinnamon chocolate cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients.
In a sauce pan, combine water, oil, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 15-20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: poling's apple crisp
directions: Mix altogether and add 1 egg and 1 cup chopped apples.
The red apples are the best for this.

title: ham ball
directions: In a small bowl, mix cream cheese, mustard and mayonnaise. Fold in ham.
Form into a ball and chill.
Before serving, you can add roasted pecans on it.
Serve with crackers.

title: olive spread
directions: Cream together.
Use with crackers or party size bread.

title: ken's chuck roast
directions: Pierce half-frozen roast with fork repeatedly.
Rub real good with garlic salt and flour.
Brown roast in Dutch oven with onion. After brown, put enough water to cover roast in Dutch oven.
Add sliced carrots and celery; simmer slow for about 1 hour.
Add potatoes and simmer 1/2 hour.
Thicken gravy with flour.
Enjoy.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt; stir in a little of milk to moisten.
Add yolks; stir gradually into hot milk.
Boil 1 minute.
Add butter and vanilla; cool.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken) together in bowl.
Dip chicken in mixture and place in baking pan.
Pour remainder of mixture on top of chicken parts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour, covering with foil for first half hour.
Serve with rice. (Do not salt chicken.)

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together fruits and pecans.
Mix 1/2 box instant pudding with 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days.

title: oreo "freakout"
directions: Crumble Oreos and put all except a few in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Press down to form a crust.
Mix pudding and 3 cups milk together; blend with mixer.
Add cream cheese; blend.
Add powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Add Cool Whip; put pudding mixture over Oreos.
Sprinkle remaining Oreos on top; refrigerate.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and put in greased loaf pan.
Cook 1 hour.
Great toasted.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Serves 5.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Cook for 40 minutes at low heat.
You will need 2 dozen buns.

title: cheddar cheese krispies
directions: Cream first two ingredients.
It helps to melt one stick of butter.
Add next three ingredients and knead until well blended. Knead in Rice Kripsies.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix bran, flour, sugar, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add beaten eggs, shortening, butter and milk; mix well.
Fill baking cups 2/3 full. Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Partially drain pineapple and spread on top of pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Sprinkle walnuts on top of cake mix.
Dice butter and sprinkle over walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before serving.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: For Roux:
Melt one stick oleo; lightly brown with 2 tablespoons flour and set aside.

title: cruckici(polish bow ties)
directions: Mix together, then cut into strips and deep fry.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Layer chicken in buttered baking dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together; spread over chicken.
Mix oleo and cracker crumbs; spread over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hidden sloppy joes
directions: Preheat oven to 375° on Bake.
Lightly grease, or spray with Pam, a Bundt cake pan.
Wash, peel and chop onion.
Place the chopped onion in a frypan.
Place ground beef in the frypan with the chopped onion and brown the meat over a medium heat.
When the meat has browned, then turn the heat down to a lower temperature and drain the oil from the browned meat into an empty can.
Measure the catsup, mustard and soup and add to the frypan with the meat. Simmer and stir the meat and sauce mixture over a medium heat for 5 minutes.
Crack eggs in a small bowl and beat them with a rotary beater.
Place the beaten eggs in a small mixing bowl.
Measure milk, margarine and Bisquick and add to the beaten eggs.
Stir the batter mixture until it is smooth.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Wash and drain kraut.
Mix all ingredients together.
Best if made day before serving.

title: chicken in cranberry sauce
directions: Marinade:
Thoroughly mix onion soup, cranberry sauce and dressing.
Place chicken in dish; marinate for 5 or 6 hours or overnight.

title: pickled beets
directions: First scrub fresh beets, then boil until tender.
Skin and cool.

title: delicious cookies(makes approximately 75 cookies)
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add egg, oil and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and tartar together and add to creamed mixture. Blend well. Add oatmeal and coconut.
Fold in Rice Krispies and chips.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes by dropping teaspoon size mounds on ungreased cookie sheets. Let cool 2 minutes on pan, then remove to a rack.

title: beef and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed in boiling water until tender. Drain and set aside until ready to combine with beef.
Brown beef and drain well.
Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Combine beef, onion and pepper with salt and flour.
Add wine, chili sauce and Worcestershire sauce and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Toss with cooked and drained macaroni.
Fold in the cheese, reserving enough cheese to garnish.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve 1 large box lemon or lime jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Place in refrigerator until it thickens slightly.
In a bowl, mix cottage cheese, miniature marshmallows, crushed pineapple with juice, light mayonnaise and chopped nuts.
When jello starts to congeal, add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into mold and return to refrigerator for at least 4 hours.

title: snickers salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Chill until served.

title: salade nicoise
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with vinegar; let stand 1 hour.
In another bowl, toss tomatoes and green beans with vinaigrette.
Let stand 1 hour.
Arrange salad greens on platter.
Place potatoes in center; surround with tomatoes and green beans.
Garnish with anchovies, capers and olives.
Serves 4.

title: baked chicken
directions: Melt butter; add spices.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Brush on butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese canapes
directions: Mix Bac*Os, cheese, onion and chili sauce thoroughly.
Spread on crackers.
Place on rack of broiler pan.
Set oven control at broil.
Place 3 to 4 inches from heat.
Toast 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: okra surprise
directions: Melt oleo
in
a large skillet.
Add other ingredients, cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Bring to boil all ingredients EXCEPT the orange juice.	Simmer for 10 minutes and remove spices.
Add 1 cup orange juice.	Store in refrigerator.
Serve hot or cold.

title: tuna-cheese biscuit bake
directions: *Or use 1 or 2 cups cooked cubed chicken, turkey or ham.
I also add a vegetable (10 ounce package, cooked) that goes well with cheese sauce; i.e. broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, Brussels sprouts, etc.

title: children's play clay
directions: Stir together baking soda and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add water and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. When mixture is consistency of moist mashed potatoes (10 to 15 minutes), turn out on a plate and cover with a damp cloth.
As soon as play clay cools enough to handle, pat until it is smooth, then it's
ready to use.
Make shapes and designs, color with food coloring or paint.
Great for Christmas ornaments.
Can protect with varnish or clear nail polish.

title: strawberry-rhubarb cobbler
directions: Mix rhubarb with soda.
Mix berries with sugar.
Let stand 5 minutes, then combine.
Add cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water. Boil for 1 minute.
Pour into large pie pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spoon batter onto hot fruit and spread to cover. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn, measure and put into roasting pan.
Cook brown sugar, butter and Karo until rolling boil; boil 5 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla.
Stir fast and pour over corn.
Toss and mix. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: best chocolate syrup brownies(microwave)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt.
Stir in chocolate syrup, flour and vanilla.
Add nuts and stir to blend well.
Turn into greased and lightly floured 8-inch square microwave-safe pan or dish. Microwave at High power for about 3 minutes.
Let rest for 3 minutes.
Microwave on High power for another 3 minutes and let rest for 3 minutes.
Finally microwave at High power for 2 more minutes or until batter is set and done to your liking.
Let rest in pan for a couple of minutes or until almost cool.
Cut into squares.
Remove from pan and garnish with nuts or powdered sugar. Turn dish a half turn after each 3 minutes if your microwave oven is not a rotating one.
Shield top corners of dish to assure even cooking.
Makes 16 to 18 brownies.

title: nacho popcorn
directions: Prepare popcorn as directed on package.
In bowl, combine popcorn with shredded cheese, olives and jalapeno pepper.
Makes 12 cups.

title: grape pie
directions: Make pastry for an 8-inch two crust pie. Remove skins from grapes; save skins. Put pulp in saucepan and bring to a boil. While hot, put pulp through a strainer to remove seeds. Mix strained pulp with skins and add sugar, flour, lemon juice and salt. Pour grape mixture into pastry lined pie pan. Dot with butter. Wet edge of pastry. Place top crust on filling, leaving 1/2-inch of crust hanging over edge of pan. Fold excess under edge of bottom pastry. Seal by pressing upper and lower pastry together on edge of pie pan. Build up fluted edge. Brush top crust with a mixture of milk and a little sugar. Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: holiday mints
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Knead until smooth. Shape mints in candy molds and place on baking sheets.
Cover with a paper towel and let dry. Remove from molds and store in an airtight container. Yields 6 dozen.

title: swiss turkey ham bake
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender, not brown. Blend in flour, salt, pepper, undrained mushrooms, cream and sherry. Cook and stir until thickened. Add turkey or chicken, ham and nuts. Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with cheese. Mix crumbs and butter and sprinkle around edges of casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes until brown.

title: easy chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare cake mix using package directions.
Cool and cut in 2-inch squares.
Prepare pudding mix using package directions. Layer cake cubes, pudding, strawberry preserves and whipped topping, with whipped topping on top.
Decorate with fresh strawberries and almonds.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello and water; while hot, add sherbet.
Chill.
When jello begins to thicken, add fruits and marshmallows.

title: cream pie(any flavor)
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Sprinkle with water, toss lightly with fork.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) round cake pans.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: You can add a few drops lemon juice.

title: chicago crunchy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Beat butter, margarine, brown and granulated sugars, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Stir in flour mixture alternating with oil until mixed.
Stir in corn flakes, oats and chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: no-knead whole wheat bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in honey; add butter, salt and whole wheat flour.
Beat on low speed until well blended.
Stir in all-purpose flour.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Stir 30 strokes with a spoon; pour batter into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch bread pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until batter reaches edge of pan, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: soft molasses cookies*and your better best.
directions: Advice:
Let the children play with the dough and flour. Results are surprising.

title: gin's chicken and dressing
directions: In small saucepan, cook butter, onion and celery for about 30 minutes on medium to low heat.
Crumble cornbread and loaf bread together.
Pour chicken broth over breads.
Add cream of chicken soup and 1/2 cup water.
Mix well.
Add butter, onion and celery and mix well.
Add sage.
Cook at 400° to 450° for 45 minutes to an hour or until brown.

title: veal and apples
directions: Trim veal of excess fat.
Heat 1 tablespoon of the butter until foamy.
Saute apple slices until tender and lightly browned. Remove.
Keep warm.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine macaroni, water and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a deep 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small edge of wrap to allow steam to escape. Microwave at High 10 to 12 minutes, or until macaroni is tender, stirring after 5 minutes.
Drain well; set aside.
Place 1/4 cup butter in a 4-cup glass measure; microwave, uncovered, at High 55 seconds or until melted.
Blend in flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt, stirring until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk; microwave, uncovered, at High 5 to 6 minutes, or until thickened, stirring after every minute.
Add cheese, stirring until melted; stir in pimiento.

title: zesty broccoli salad
directions: Undercook the broccoli.
Drain and cool.
Mix with all the remaining ingredients and chill.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together. Chill.

title: potato soup
directions: Pour entire potato mixture including broth into white sauce. Simmer on low. Do not let scorch.

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle meat tenderizer onto steaks.
Cut steaks into 1-inch strips.
Place oil in hot skillet.
Put steak strips into skillet and brown.
Cut peppers and onions into strips and add to meat. Add Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Add stir-fry seasoning following instructions on package.
Simmer until peppers and onions are cooked.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and salt with water; let stand 2 hours. Drain and add, sugar, vinegar, 1 cup water, mustard and celery seed, ginger and turmeric.
Cook until tender (do not overcook). Pour in jars and seal immediately.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease
a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Dump undrained
pineapple
in
pan;
spread
evenly.
Dump in cherry pie
filling
and spread into even layer.
Crumble dry cake mix onto cherry layer, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Put
butter
slices
evenly all over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Add rice to milk.
Cook, covered, in top of double boiler, until rice is tender.
Beat egg yolks.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Stir some of the rice mix into beaten yolks, then add yolks to hot mixture.
Cook for 2 minutes; stir constantly. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Fold beaten whites into custard.
Chill and serve.

title: quick pasta side dish
directions: Boil noodles for least time listed in directions (a little stiff). Drain, rinse in cold water to cool noodles and in mix in dressing. Chill for 20-30 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste. You can try different variations to this recipe to taste (i.e. add mixed vegetables, bacon bits, or use different dressings).

title: easy chicken breast
directions: Place 1 chicken breast on foil.
Top with dressing, a slice of tomato, pat of butter, garlic powder, lemon juice, salt, pepper and shredded cheese.
Wrap.
Repeat for additional pieces.
Bake 425° for 30-45 mins.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Brush bread with melted butter before spreading cucumber mixture.

title: chicken italiano
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, place oil, mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Microwave at High (10) for 2 to 4 minutes until tender. Add chicken.
Microwave at High (10) for 6 to 8 minutes.
Turn over.
Add wine or chicken broth, Italian seasoning and basil. Microwave at Medium (5) for 5 to 8 minutes.
Spread spaghetti sauce over chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan and red pepper flakes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1 cup pecans. Refrigerate until well chilled, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, then form into ball and roll in remaining chopped pecans. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and oleo.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, then marshmallow cream.
Add vanilla.
Beat well and pour into greased pan.

title: low-fat gingerbread
directions: Blend molasses, egg substitute and buttermilk together.
Sift the dry ingredients together and gradually add to liquid ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture in a Bundt pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bring chicken to boil, then simmer 45 minutes. After cools, pick chicken off the bones (can use boneless). Melt butter in casserole dish. Layer 1/2 bag of crumbs (Pepperidge Farm), chicken and soup, then add the rest of crumbs as topping.
Pour broth over the top. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: my favorite summer salad(serves 8)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water. Add sherbet; blend well. Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in pineapple and oranges. Turn into 2-quart mold; chill until firm. Unmold; garnish as desired.

title: gay's original cashew chicken
directions: Drain water chestnuts, bamboo shoots and pimientos.
In a large cast-iron Dutch oven, stir-fry chicken in oil until tender. Add chopped onion, celery and bell pepper.
Saute until tender. Add bamboo shoots and water chestnuts.
Cool altogether for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in cashews and pimientos.
Add 4 to 5 cans broth.
Bring to a boil; cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Mix garlic powder and cornstarch with soy sauce; blend well.
Add to chicken. Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: french pancakes
directions: Combine the beaten eggs, salt and melted butter.
Add the milk or water, a little at a time to the mixture.
Use like any other pancake batter.
The batter will be very thin.

title: fruit and nut bread pudding
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
In large bowl, combine bread and sugar.
Set aside.
In another bowl, beat eggs, milk, cinnamon, salt and vanilla until foamy.
Pour over bread and sugar; mix well. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Cut apple pie slices in half.
Stir apple slices and all remaining ingredients into chilled mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm or cold with whipped topping or ice cream. Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: petits choux
directions: Put fat and water in a small saucepan and stir over high heat until fat is melted and liquid is boiling rapidly.
Add flour all at once.
Raise saucepan a few inches over heat and stir briskly. The paste will come away from the sides of pan and form a smooth ball in center.
Cook, stirring for 30 seconds longer.

title: after dinner mint pie
directions: Using a metal spatula, fill crumb crust with 1 1/2 cups softened ice cream.
Freeze to harden.
Spread 3/4 cup Mrs. R's Hot Fudge Topping (room temperature) on hardened ice cream.
Freeze. Repeat with second layer, using 1 1/2 cups ice cream.
Spread with whipped topping.
Serve frozen.
Garnish with chocolate curls.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Pour sugar over cabbage and onions.
Mix together vinegar, oil, sugar, salt, mustard and bring to a boil.
Pour over chopped cabbage and onions.
Put a tight lid over cabbage mixture and put in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.

title: strawberry preserves
